When every U.S. president faces his first midterm election, his party&#39;s number of seats in Congress often decreases.
According to a new poll released by the Washington Post and ABC News on the 4th, although the Democrats still maintain an advantage in the House of Representatives, Republicans can benefit from economic assessment and Trump’s views on border security. benefit from rigorous attention.
Polls show that registered voters prefer Democratic House candidates to Republicans, 50% to 43%, but this is still down from a 14-point lead in August.
