China announced that it will reduce import tariffs on 1,585 tax items starting from November 1, 2018.
Since the beginning of this year, China has successively taken the initiative to reduce import tariffs.
On May 1st this year, a comprehensive tax reduction on drugs was implemented, and the import tariffs for a total of 28 tax items, including anti-cancer drugs, all common drugs, alkaloid drugs with anti-cancer effects, and actually imported Chinese patent medicines, were adjusted to zero.
At the same time, the value-added tax burden on the production and import of anti-cancer drugs has been significantly reduced.
On July 1, taxes will be reduced on 218 tax items of automobiles and parts.
After the tax reduction, China&#39;s vehicle tax rate has been lower than the average level of developing countries, which is in line with the reality of China&#39;s automobile industry.
This tax reduction will promote industry structural adjustment and optimal allocation of resources, accelerate the survival of the fittest, and help improve the quality of products and services. It is expected to promote automobile price adjustments to a certain extent and provide consumers with more benefits.
On July 1, taxes will be reduced on 1,449 tax items for daily consumer goods.
Tax reductions on daily consumer goods are closely related to people&#39;s needs for a better life.
This tax reduction is not only large in quantity but also powerful, with an average tax reduction of 56%.
Tax reductions on daily consumer goods will directly benefit consumers and help domestic industries improve their competitiveness.
On November 1, tax reductions will be implemented on 1,585 tax items of mechanical and electrical equipment, parts and components, raw materials and other industrial products.
Appropriately reducing import tariffs on some urgently needed domestic industrial products can attract more foreign investment, help increase domestic effective supply, and help industrial upgrading. It will also help companies allocate resources globally and reduce production costs. It will also help Reduce the pressure on the domestic environment.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Tariff Commission Office of the State Council of China, the above four independent tax reductions, as well as the third step tax reduction implemented on July 1 this year based on the results of the negotiations to expand the scope of the information technology agreement, will make China’s overall tariff level drop from the previous year. of 9.8% dropped to 7.5%.
The adjusted overall tariff level is slightly higher than that of the EU, lower than that of most developing countries, and is at a moderately low level, basically matching China&#39;s developing country status and development stage.
According to the person in charge, the overall level of tariffs, as one of the important indicators of the degree of openness of China’s goods trade, should be adapted to China’s economic development stage and reflect the characteristics of the times.
China ranks first in the world in terms of trade in goods and has the economic foundation to further open up. However, the quality and efficiency of trade development still lag behind those of developed economies. Therefore, the overall level of tariffs should be appropriately reduced.
Tariffs are a means of protection for compliance. Tariff levels should be compatible with industrial competitiveness and healthy competition should be encouraged. Over-protection is not conducive to industrial development and quality improvement.
The adjustment of tariff rates must take into account both production needs and consumer needs.
Focus on reducing tax rates on commodities with large domestic demand that are conducive to industrial transformation and upgrading, and strive to increase the import of specialty and advantageous products for which the people&#39;s needs are relatively concentrated, continuously enhance the sense of gain for enterprises and the public, and meet the needs of upgrading the industrial structure and consumption structure.
Tax reduction efforts must take into account the affordability of fiscal revenue and industrial development.
In the selection of specific tax reduction products and tax reduction ranges, it is necessary to coordinate the domestic and foreign markets, the upstream and downstream aspects, and the relationship between production and consumption to maintain the stable and positive development momentum of China&#39;s economy.
The person in charge emphasized that this year marks the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up. China&#39;s initiative to reduce the overall level of import tariffs is a major measure based on China&#39;s own needs to achieve high-quality development. It is conducive to the coordinated use of both international and foreign resources, promoting the improvement of the quality of the domestic supply system, and meeting the needs of the country. The consumption upgrade needs of the people.
This action and measure shows that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win opening strategy, firmly support economic globalization, resolutely safeguard the principles of free trade and the multilateral trading system with the WTO as the core, and continue to draw development momentum from opening up to the world. It also allows China’s development to better benefit the world.
Serbia has announced that it has entered the highest state of combat readiness. The President of Serbia and Russia will meet tomorrow to discuss the situation in Kosovo.
Nantong News Agency quoted the Serbian Presidential Office as saying that Serbian President Vucic ordered the country&#39;s armed forces to enter the highest state of combat readiness in view of the Kosovo Special Forces occupying the access to the Gazivoda Hydropower Station Reservoir Lake controlled by Belgrade in northern Kosovo. .
On September 29, Serbian Defense Minister Vulin declared that the Serbian army has entered a state of full combat readiness.
Vulin emphasized that as long as the order issued by Vucic remains valid, Serbia will continue to monitor the current situation in Kosovo, and no matter which direction the situation develops, the Serbian army will respond.
According to the Russian TASS news agency, on September 29, Vucic said in an interview that he had informed the United States, Russia and Europe of the current situation and would go to Moscow to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin on October 2 to discuss the Kosovo issue. to seek Putin’s support.
When asked whether Serbia needs military support from Russia like Syria, Vucic gave a negative answer: &quot;I don&#39;t want a major military conflict on our territory. &quot;
Vucic also said that the Serbian army entered a state of full combat readiness only to form a deterrent to prevent conflicts from occurring, but it was also a clear warning: Any violence in Kosovo will never be tolerated.
The reason why the Serbian army has improved its combat readiness is related to two major actions taken by Kosovo.
According to Serbia, in recent days, Albanians have been arresting Serbs who have lived there for generations in northern Kosovo, and these arrested Serbs have not violated any laws.
Vucic said that since Marko Juric, the head of the Serbian government’s Kosovo and Metohija office, was beaten and detained by the Kosovo Albanian army on March 26 this year, the Albanians have continued to escalate the situation in the region and carried out inhumane acts against the Serbs. arrests and deportations.
In addition, more than 100 people, including the ROSU special forces of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Republic of Kosovo, armed police and snipers, which were recently self-declared, occupied positions near the storage lake of the Gazivoda Hydropower Station and entered the ecological and ecological environment near the embankment in the northern part of Kosovo. Sports Center and blocked all nearby roads in areas originally controlled by Serbia.
Vucic pointed out that Kosovo’s military adventure was instigated by Western countries. The Kosovo army’s actions were not notified to Serbia in advance, which violated paragraph 1 of Chapter 9 of the Brussels Agreement and also violated adopted United Nations Security Council Resolution 1244 and the military-technical agreement between Seko.
Vucic has already called out NATO Secretary-General Stoltenberg, criticizing Western countries&#39; hypocritical rhetoric on the Kosovo issue.
The root cause of the current conflict is still the centuries-old historical grudge between the Serbian and Albanian communities in Kosovo.
Regarding the ownership of Kosovo, the Serbs and Albanians each have their own opinions.
Serbia regards Kosovo as the birthplace of the nation and the cradle of culture, because Serbia established its most powerful country here in the 12th century, and ethnic Albanians only immigrated in large numbers after the invasion of the Ottoman Empire and the defeat of the Serbian army in the north.
The Albanian people insist that the Illyrians, the primitive tribe who lived in Kosovo in the 4th and 5th centuries BC, are the ancestors of the Albanian people. Therefore, Kosovo has been the territory of the Albanian people since ancient times.
Subjective political divisions have resulted in fierce conflicts between different ethnic groups, religions and cultures, and fierce confrontation between Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo.
In 1912, Kosovo Albanians first declared Albania&#39;s independence.
After the First World War, a large number of Albanians living in the Balkan Peninsula moved to Turkey, and the proportion of Serbs increased relatively. In the eyes of the Serbs, the practice of &quot;just taking back their own land&quot; was regarded by the Albanians as &quot;a big deal&quot;. The plunder of Serbianism&quot; intensified the conflicts between the two ethnic groups.
Kosovo has become the &quot;powder keg&quot; of the Balkans.
In 1999, armed conflicts broke out between Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army and the Serbian army and police, which led to NATO forces bombing the Yugoslavia Federation composed of Serbia and Montenegro, and the Kosovo War broke out.
On February 17, 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared independence from Serbia.
Although there was news that Serbia would normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, due to historical national grievances and geopolitical constraints, the agreement was not able to be signed due to the constraints of the United States, Europe, Russia and other parties. .
Just a month ago, Vucic made it clear for the first time that he advocated the separation of Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo, once again making the conflict between the two communities public.
Power and communication are still interrupted, Indonesia&#39;s strong earthquake and tsunami make rescue difficult
According to figures released by the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency in the early morning of the 30th, a strong earthquake and resulting tsunami in Donggala County, Central Sulawesi Province, the country on the 28th, has killed 420 people.
Wilem Rampangliei, head of the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency, said that this number is only a preliminary statistics from Palu, the capital of Central Sulawesi, about 80 kilometers away from the epicenter. Due to the lack of large-scale search and rescue machinery, many hotels, shopping malls, shopping malls, etc. in the city collapsed and were damaged by the earthquake. Warehouses and other densely populated buildings have not yet been searched and rescued.
On September 29, 2018 local time, in Palu, Indonesia, a bridge damaged by an earthquake and tsunami collapsed and broke into several sections.
Due to severe damage to power and communication facilities, the epicenter of the earthquake, Donggala County and the adjacent Xiji area are still &quot;isolated islands&quot; that cannot be contacted, and the number of victims cannot be counted.
According to media reports here, Indonesian Vice President Kalla said the death toll may reach thousands.
Power interruption, communication interruption, road blockage, airport damage... Rescue work after strong earthquakes and tsunamis is full of difficulties.
Due to power outages, some hospitals and relief sites in Palu rely on fuel to generate electricity.
The roads in and out of the city were blocked by landslides, making it impossible for large transport vehicles including oil tankers to enter, making fuel supply very tight.
Indonesian Social Minister Agus said that due to road damage, the ministry mobilized emergency relief materials such as tents, mattresses, blankets, clothes, food, and household kits from South Sulawesi and Gorontalo provinces adjacent to the earthquake area. It has not yet arrived in the disaster area.
Disaster relief materials deployed from the capital Jakarta are being transported to the disaster area via air force transport planes.
In view of the damage to the Palu Airport control tower and runway in the earthquake, in order to ensure safety and ensure rescue, all commercial flights have been grounded, and only military aircraft transporting relief supplies and personnel can take off and land.
Indonesian Coordinating Minister for Political, Legal and Security Affairs Wiranto, who is directing the rescue in the earthquake area, requested that power supply and airport commercial flight services be restored as soon as possible to ensure the operation of hospitals and other rescue institutions, so that more rescue workers, volunteers, and aid supplies can be transported Arrive at the disaster area.
On the 28th, multiple strong earthquakes occurred in Donggala County, Central Sulawesi Province, Indonesia. Among them, a 7.7-magnitude earthquake that occurred at 17:02 local time triggered a tsunami, causing tsunamis in Palu City, Donggala County, and Sigi areas. Major disaster.
China News Service, Beijing, October 1 (Reporter Yin Li) The sky is clear and blue, the sky is clear, and the sky is full of colorful clouds... Recently, Beijing has continued to turn on the most beautiful blue sky mode, attracting thousands of Beijing residents to show off pictures on social platforms. He continued to express his happiness on the screen, saying, &quot;Under the blue sky and white clouds, the &#39;drunk&#39; skyline is the best business card of Beijing.&quot;
Since August, Beijing has welcomed the “bluest sky”.
Within the capital, people can be seen taking photos anytime, anywhere, with smartphones or SLR cameras.
On social platforms such as Weibo and WeChat Moments, you can see the Forbidden City, Tiananmen Square, Bird&#39;s Nest, Hutongs, etc. in the lenses of netizens everywhere... Various buildings show different beauties against the blue sky.
Some netizens said that such &quot;scenery blockbusters&quot; are the best city promotional videos in Beijing; some netizens joked that if such blue skies flooded the screen for a long time, people with cervical spondylosis would be cured; some netizens hoped that &quot; This touch of blue can survive winter and welcome spring and summer, making the sky of the capital blue all year round.&quot;
Why do people in Beijing love to bask in the blue sky so much?
Just because people living in this city suffered from smog in the past, they were particularly eager for blue skies. However, after the &quot;Blue Sky Defense War&quot; was launched in Beijing and the air quality was continuously improved, the smog became less and the blue skies became more. The joy in my eyes is in my heart, and the happiness I get is particularly weighty.
