According to the plan, officials continue to guide the decentralization of non-capital functions, promote clean energy substitution and pollution reduction, and eliminate a total of 4,923 coal-fired boilers.
Beijing has thus become the first major city in mainland China to realize natural gas supply throughout the entire network.
Data show that between 2013 and 2017, Beijing’s average annual concentration of PM2.5 dropped by 35.6%; the number of days with air quality standards increased by 50; the number of days with first-class quality increased by 25; and the number of days with heavy pollution decreased by 35 days. The incidence of pollution is significantly reduced.
While air quality continues to improve, Beijing officials released the &quot;Beijing Three-Year Action Plan to Win the Blue Sky Defense War&quot; in September this year based on a new round of PM2.5 source analysis. In view of the current treatment stage and pollution characteristics, the focus is on diesel Trucks, dust, volatile organic compound control and other key prevention and control areas, optimize and adjust the transportation structure, industrial structure, energy structure and land use structure, strengthen regional joint prevention and control, strive to strengthen urban refined management, comprehensively promote green development, and strive to make the &quot;bluest bluest&quot; &quot;Sky&quot; is permanently stationed in the capital, no longer &quot;things are rare but valuable&quot;, allowing it to return to being the background in people&#39;s photo albums rather than the protagonist.
