From a tourism symbol to a digital economic symbol, what has Wuzhen experienced in these years?
As the permanent site of the World Internet Conference, how Wuzhen can successfully undertake the dividends of the summit has attracted much attention.
In the five years since the first World Internet Conference, Wuzhen’s changes have been obvious to all.
In 2014, there were only 12 companies related to the digital economy and the Internet in the town. By the third quarter of this year, there were more than 500 companies.
This is a microcosm of Wuzhen’s development of digital economy.
The convening of the Internet Conference allows local companies to receive inspiration from the digital economy and the wave of digitization at a close distance. The desire of enterprises to transform and upgrade is very strong. Traditional manufacturing companies have increased investment and research and development in aspects such as machine replacement and intelligent management.
Jiang Wei, Secretary of the Wuzhen Town Party Committee, said that Wuzhen will build a new economic empowerment center in the future.
The development of the digital economy cannot be separated from the support of infrastructure.
This year, Wuzhen launched 5G pilot work on the basis of achieving full coverage of 4G communication networks and free WiFi.
At the same time, Tongxiang City, where Wuzhen is located, is the first county-level city in the country to build a dedicated international Internet data channel, and has also become a hot spot for the development of the Internet industry.
Since the first World Internet Conference, Tongxiang has introduced a total of 565 digital economy projects with a total planned investment of 37.725 billion yuan. In the first three quarters of this year, the core manufacturing industry of the digital economy achieved a total output value of 8.73 billion yuan, with an added value that increased by 13% year-on-year.
&quot;Wuzhen was a tourism symbol before, but later it became a drama and cultural symbol. Because of the Internet Conference, it has now become a symbol of the Internet and digital economy. &quot;
Sheng Yongjun, Secretary of the Tongxiang Municipal Party Committee, believes that the dividends of the World Internet Conference have accumulated over time. Therefore, it is more necessary to build a platform to undertake the overlapping introduction of talents, projects, technologies and other elements from all parties.
Shen Yi, a native of Tongxiang, has been working outside the country for 20 years. Because of her connection with the Internet Conference, she returned to her hometown to start a business.
On December 2 last year, he entered the 4th Internet Light Expo with a high-capacity tamper-proof digital technology solution, which was favored by many customers.
Shen Yi chose to start a business in Wuzhen not only because of her hometown complex, &quot;In Wuzhen, recruiting people is easier than I thought, and our applications are also implemented quickly. Our applications are included in the Wuzhen smart parking project. &quot;
A Wuzhen Avenue shows the spillover effect of the Internet Conference.
This avenue running through the north and south of Tongxiang not only connects tourist attractions, but is also an industrial avenue.
Relying on it, Wuzhen Avenue Science and Technology Innovation Cluster came into being.
The reporter learned that in the future, Wuzhen Avenue will become the main front for Tongxiang’s industrial development, taking the lead in applying a large number of achievements such as smart medical care, smart elderly care, and smart government affairs, and gathering industries that account for 80% of the city’s GDP and many high-level talents.
