With active treatment, the survival rate of premature infants aged 29 weeks and above in China reaches 98%, which has reached the level of developed countries.
China News Service, Shanghai, September 30 (Chen Jing, Luo Yanqian) The National Children&#39;s Medical Center and the Children&#39;s Hospital of Fudan University disclosed on the 30th that they have introduced Canada&#39;s advanced methods in the &quot;China NICU Hospitalized Premature Infant Outcome Quality Improvement Project&quot;.
Project results show that with active treatment, the survival rate of premature infants aged 29 weeks and above in China reaches 98%, which has reached the level of developed countries. However, there is still much room for improvement in the complication-free survival rate of extremely small gestational age premature infants and premature infants.
In the past 20 years, the Chinese government has been paying attention to the treatment of newborns.
At present, the infant mortality rate in Shanghai has dropped to 3.71 ‰, which is significantly lower than the national average and has reached the advanced level of developed countries.
Through four years of unremitting efforts, the &quot;China NICU Hospitalized Premature Infants Prognosis Quality Improvement Project&quot; has greatly improved the quality of life of premature infants.
Professor Cao Yun, director of the Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU) of the Children&#39;s Hospital of Fudan University, told reporters that while improving the survival rate of premature infants, attention should be paid to reducing the survival quality of premature infants, reducing the incidence of complications, improving neurodevelopmental prognosis, and improving patient outcomes. The overall outcome of infants is of great significance to improving the overall quality of life and population quality of premature infants. It is an important issue of concern to the pediatric and neonatology circles at home and abroad, and is also a key issue of this project.
Through four years of unremitting efforts, the &quot;China NICU Hospitalized Premature Infant Outcomes Quality Improvement Project&quot; has included tens of thousands of premature infants with a gestational age of 33 weeks and below across the country, reducing the domestic mortality rate of premature infants with small gestational age and small birth weight by one-third. At the same time, the incidence of serious complications in premature infants has dropped significantly, greatly improving the quality of life of premature infants.
By establishing a national neonatal quality improvement collaboration network and introducing the concept of collaborative quality improvement, the project has radiated 25 collaborating hospitals across China and established a complete set of collaborative methods suitable for domestic conditions to improve the prognosis of premature infants and improve the level of neonatal care. Systematic and effective collaborative quality improvement approach.
The Children&#39;s Hospital of Fudan University is joining forces with neonatology departments across the country to formulate guidelines for the diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections based on the experience accumulated through the project, providing reference and guidance for the standardized diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections in China.
It is understood that in the &quot;China Preterm Infant Prognosis Quality Improvement Project&quot;, the pediatric hospital has introduced the EPIQ method into 25 large-scale NICUs in 19 provinces across the country, aiming to solve the problem of premature infant infections that plagues China&#39;s neonatal intensive care units.
After more than 10 years of continuous improvement, the complication-free survival rate of premature infants in Canada has increased by about one-third. Canada is now among the countries with the best prognosis for premature infants in the world.
The EPIQ method is now used in all NICUs across Canada and has been adopted by 6 countries.
The pediatric hospital revealed that research results showed that after two years of EPIQ intervention, infections in premature infants dropped by 35%, while the use of antibiotics dropped by 20%.
In the future, the Children&#39;s Hospital of Fudan University will continue to promote and implement this method nationwide, aiming to comprehensively reduce the incidence of all complications in premature infants and improve the quality of neonatal care nationwide.
At present, it is an indisputable fact that there are differences and inhomogeneities in the treatment levels in various regions in China.
According to Professor Cao Yun, as an important construction unit of the National Children&#39;s Medical Center, the Children&#39;s Hospital will play a leading role. This research covers Xinjiang, Guizhou, Gansu, Shaanxi and other western provinces, with a view to gradually promoting neonatal treatment nationwide. of homogenization and standardization.
It is understood that the Children&#39;s Hospital of Fudan University is joining forces with neonatology departments across the country to formulate guidelines for the diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections based on accumulated experience from the project, to provide reference and guidance for the standardized diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections in China.
According to reports, in 2019, the China Neonatal Collaboration Network, whose coordination center is located at the Children&#39;s Hospital of Fudan University, will unite 63 hospitals across the country to carry out the next stage of national quality improvement, with a view to promoting the uniform development of China&#39;s neonatal care levels.
Wu Jinglei, director of the Shanghai Municipal Health and Family Planning Commission, said that Shanghai&#39;s ability to become a central city in the center of Asia is not only reflected in research, but also in the construction of the entire service system. Service quality and service results should have a place in Asia, thus truly reflecting China&#39;s medical level. .
Xin Shiping: Build a &quot;hero monument&quot; in your heart - written on the fifth Martyrs&#39; Day.
On September 30, the eve of the 69th birthday of the Republic, we ushered in the fifth Martyrs&#39; Day. Xi Jinping and other party and state leaders came to Tiananmen Square to attend a ceremony of laying flower baskets to the people&#39;s heroes.
At this moment, no matter where you are, please pay tribute to the heroes.
An anniversary is a time to relive and wake up.
Looking through the rich history, behind the name of every martyr is a living life.
They also have passionate youth, sincere love, and caring family members.
However, because they firmly believe that &quot;the doctrine we believe in is the truth of the universe&quot; and in order to &quot;avoid the suffering of the next generation&quot;, they are willing to sacrifice everything they have.
&quot;Every day I live, I have to shout for China.&quot;
Traveling through time and space, the heroes set up spiritual road signs to guide the way forward.
&quot;Where do you come from, where do you go?&quot; &quot;What kind of person do you want to be?&quot; It is not difficult to get the answers by understanding the heroes.
To commemorate the heroes, the most important thing is to build a &quot;hero monument&quot; in our hearts.
According to incomplete statistics, since the revolutionary war years, approximately 20 million martyrs have heroically sacrificed their lives for national independence, people&#39;s liberation, and national prosperity.
Due to various reasons, many martyrs did not even leave their names.
Countless heroes have watered their ideals with their blood and practiced their beliefs with their lives. Remembering their heroic names and passing on their spirit are to protect the roots and soul of the nation.
This &quot;hero monument&quot; cannot be defaced or damaged in any way.
For some time, undercurrents such as historical nihilism and pan-entertainment have been surging.
Various practices that distort history and belittle heroes and martyrs challenge justice and conscience, confuse value judgments, and arouse public indignation and vigilance across society.
Heroes cannot be desecrated, and heroes cannot be forgotten.
Behaviors that touch the bottom line cannot be left unchecked. We must dare to use the sword to defend the dignity of heroes and martyrs with the rule of law and justice.
On May 1 this year, the Law on the Protection of Heroes and Martyrs was officially implemented.
From the perspective of judicial practice, the judgments in some cases are very popular, which not only effectively safeguard the glorious image of heroes and martyrs in accordance with the law, but also release the positive energy of advocating heroes and admiring martyrs.
A nation with aspirations cannot be without heroes, and a country with ideals cannot be without pioneers.
Remembering the martyrs and calling for heroes has become a common social consensus.
Currently, there are millions of memorial facilities of various types across the country, and more than 100 million people visit the Martyrs Cemetery every year.
