China News Service, Sapporo, September 30. After defeating Cuba 3:0 in the first game, the Chinese women&#39;s volleyball team defeated Turkey 3:0 again on the 30th, winning two consecutive victories in the 2018 World Championships group stage.
But compared with the first battle, this battle of the Chinese women&#39;s volleyball team is more difficult and dangerous.
There are 24 teams participating in the 2018 Women&#39;s Volleyball World Championship. The Chinese Women&#39;s Volleyball Team is in Group B with Italy, Turkey, Bulgaria, Canada and Cuba.
Judging from the world rankings and overall strength of the teams in Group B, the Turkish team and the Italian team are the main opponents of the Chinese team.
After the game started that day, the Chinese team entered the state quickly and took the lead at the beginning. They maintained their advantage throughout the game and put a lot of pressure on their opponents in serving and blocking. They won the first game smoothly with 25:18.
In the second game, the Turkish team entered the state and served very fiercely. They took a 6:2 lead at the beginning. After the Chinese team requested a timeout, they adjusted their formation and gradually tied the score to 7. Then they blocked the ball many times and scored 7:0. The scoring surge; at the end of the game, the Turkish team once chased the score to 15:19; after the Chinese team got the game point at 24:20, the tenacious Turkish team chased for 2 points in a row; after the Chinese team requested a timeout again, with Zhu Ting&#39;s The running attack scored and won the second game 25:23.
The situation in the third game was very stalemate, with the scores of both sides rising alternately, and it was tied at 19 at one point.
At the critical moment, the Turkish team made a mistake. After the Chinese team led 21:19, it relied on Zhu Ting&#39;s powerful smash and Zhang Changning&#39;s offense to win the match point at 24:21; then the Turkish team chased the score to 23:24, and the Chinese team After requesting a timeout, Zhang Changning scored on offense, and the Chinese team secured the victory at 25:23.
The head coach of the Chinese women&#39;s volleyball team, Lang Ping, said frankly after the game that the whole game was not easy.
&quot;We are well prepared and have good blocking skills. The Turkish team has relatively comprehensive skills. We must reduce our mistakes and strive to win by scoring on our own initiative. &quot;
Facing familiar teammates from the past, Zhu Ting, who plays for Turkey&#39;s Vakif Bank team, suffered a lot of restrictions in the first game of the game that day. Then she took the initiative to make changes and still played a powerful offense.
&quot;We are very familiar with each other, and it is normal to be marked by the opponent, but the Chinese team played to the extreme, blocking and attacking very well even when the first pass was not smooth. &quot;
Next, the Chinese women&#39;s volleyball team will take a day off to conduct physical and technical training; on October 2, it will face the Canadian team, its third opponent in the group stage.
