Nearly a thousand state-owned scenic spots have reduced ticket prices, and more than half have dropped prices by more than 20%.
[Abstract] As of September 28, various places have implemented or issued documents to announce to the public 981 free opening or price reduction measures for scenic spots (74 free openings, 907 price reductions), Yunnan Stone Forest, Dali Three Pagodas, Jade Dragon Snow Mountain, Guilin, Guangxi Scenic spots such as the Li River, Wuyi Mountain in Fujian, Zhangjiajie in Hunan, Terracotta Warriors and Horses in Shaanxi, Sanqing Mountain in Jiangxi, and Kanas in Xinjiang have all implemented price reductions.
In order to implement the decisions and arrangements of the Central Economic Work Conference and the &quot;Government Work Report&quot;, the National Development and Reform Commission issued the &quot;Guidance on Improving the Ticket Price Formation Mechanism of State-owned Scenic Areas and Reducing the Ticket Prices of Key State-owned Scenic Areas&quot; (hereinafter referred to as the Guidance) on June 28 Opinions), requiring the improvement of the ticket price formation mechanism for state-owned scenic spots in terms of reasonably defining the cost components of ticket pricing, innovating price management methods, and strictly implementing pricing procedures to ensure that significant results are achieved in reducing the high ticket prices of key state-owned scenic spots before the end of September.
In accordance with deployment requirements, various localities have actively carried out work and have successively reduced ticket prices for a number of key state-owned scenic spots.
As of September 28, various localities have implemented or issued documents to announce to the public free opening or price reduction measures for 981 scenic spots (74 free openings and 907 price reductions), including 159 5A-level scenic spots and 534 4A-level scenic spots. A total of 693, accounting for 70.6%.
Among the 907 scenic spots that have reduced prices, 491 have experienced price reductions of more than 20%, accounting for 54.3%, and 214 have experienced price reductions of more than 30%, accounting for 23.6%.
Yunnan, Shandong, Guangxi, Shaanxi and other provinces have a large number of price reduction scenic spots. Among them, Yunnan has more than 100 price reduction scenic spots, with an overall decrease of more than 30%.
All 5A-level scenic spots priced by the governments of Anhui, Chongqing and other eight provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) have achieved price reductions.
Scenic spots such as Yunnan Stone Forest, Dali Three Pagodas, Jade Dragon Snow Mountain, Lijiang River in Guilin, Guangxi, Wuyi Mountain in Fujian, Zhangjiajie in Hunan, Terracotta Warriors and Horses in Shaanxi, Sanqing Mountain in Jiangxi, and Kanas in Xinjiang have all implemented price reductions.
The ticket prices of key state-owned scenic spots will gradually return to a reasonable range, which will help promote the transformation and upgrading of the tourism industry from ticket economy to industrial economy, niche tourism to mass tourism, and scenic spot tourism to all-region tourism. It will also help to optimize the supply structure of the tourism industry and create tourism consumption demand. A virtuous cycle of steady expansion promotes the sustainable and healthy development of scenic spots and tourism.
The National Development and Reform Commission also emphasized that all localities should strengthen the price order and standardization of scenic spots, guide scenic spots to improve services, and ensure that price reductions do not reduce quality.
In addition, the National Development and Reform Commission has conducted special inspections on the issues reported by the media that the price of tickets for individual scenic spots has dropped too little and the prices have not been reduced, requiring all localities to deal with them seriously, respond to social concerns in a timely manner, and effectively implement price reductions.
IPIM carries out short, medium and long-term optimization work in an orderly manner
The Macau Trade and Investment Promotion Institute has submitted a short, medium and long-term optimization work report on &quot;major investment immigration&quot; and &quot;skilled immigration&quot;. In addition to stepping up the promotion and implementation of various tasks in the report, it has also continued to listen to social opinions and evaluate the report. Content and related work are continuously optimized.
IPIM will introduce relevant optimization work to all sectors of society as soon as possible.
Among them, 5 are short-term measures implemented within this year; 5 are medium-term measures implemented within 2019; and 1 is long-term measure.
In addition, IPIM has also conducted a comprehensive review of its internal management system in accordance with the instructions of the Secretary for Economy and Finance Leong Vai Tac.
The five short-term measures implemented this year include:
1. Carry out review work. Priority will be given to reviewing cases that are about to expire for 7 years, cases mentioned in ICAC reports, and newly renewed cases. If a case is found to contain signs of misconduct or illegality, it will be proactively referred to the relevant judicial authorities for follow-up handling;
2. Conduct on-site inspections of projects involving “major investment immigration”. By late September, more than 20 investment projects had been inspected;
3. Conduct a comprehensive review of the current assessment system. In terms of reviewing applications for &quot;Major Investment Immigration&quot;, six principles for analyzing investment projects have been re-established; and in terms of reviewing applications for &quot;Skilled Immigration&quot;, the elements that are conducive to the development of Macao and the conditions for priority recruitment of talents will be clearly defined. Improve relevant approval mechanisms. At the same time, a list of &quot;five industries and ten types of work&quot; has been formulated for the annual priority introduction of talents to coordinate with the policy direction of the SAR government and attract talents in a more targeted manner;
4. Continuously increase information transparency. This includes plans to gradually announce the approval criteria, scoring standards and weightings starting from the fourth quarter of this year, and further refine and make public the approval data;
5. In terms of improving the confirmation mechanism, it is required to check the work status in Macao before confirmation; for major investments, on-site verification and financial statements must be submitted.
The five medium-term measures implemented in 2019 include:
1. Establish a mechanism to regularly listen to the opinions of the Talent Development Committee and the Economic Development Committee. Among them, a working meeting was held with the Economic Development Committee in September to discuss the establishment of relevant mechanisms.
2. The applicant is required to submit financial statements prepared by an independent third party every year to continuously review the operating status of the investment project;
3. Further standardize and electronicize the case application and approval process to reduce human errors;
4. Comprehensively review the current manpower configuration and cooperate with the implementation of multiple optimization measures;
5. Speed up the research work on revising the &quot;Temporary Residence System for Investors, Managers and Specially Qualified Technical Personnel&quot;.
As for long-term measures, we will step up research on law amendments. It is expected to start drafting relevant regulations in the first half of 2019 and strive to complete them as soon as possible. We will further clarify the approval standards, review mechanisms and confirmation mechanisms for temporary residence permits, and increase the investigation function of the IPIM to be more precise. The local government approves and supervises temporary residence permit applications.
Experts from the national membraneless cotton on-site observation and seminar exchange activities walked into the test field and listened to the introduction by representatives of the team of Academician Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
China News Service, Xinjiang Shaya, September 30 (Geng Dandan and Wang Xiaojun) At the film-free cotton planting experimental base in Shaya County, Xinjiang, the growth of film-free cotton is gratifying, and it is &quot;not inferior&quot; to the mulched cotton next to it. Clusters of Snow-white cotton competes to &quot;open&quot; and hang all over the branches.
From September 27th to 28th, the national filmless cotton on-site observation and seminar exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
The reporter learned at the observation meeting that the film-free cotton technology system based on &quot;China Cotton 619&quot; and its supporting cultivation measures has initially achieved the goal of film-free planting in cotton fields and reduced the impact of residual film in Xinjiang cotton fields on the ecological environment and raw cotton. pollution, the research and demonstration of membraneless cotton comprehensive technology have made significant progress.
Academician Yu Shuxun, academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, famous cotton genetic breeder, and chief scientist of the cotton system of the National Modern Agricultural Industry Technology System, introduced the growth of film-free cotton to Zhou Guomo, secretary of the Party Committee of Zhejiang A&amp;F University.
&quot;The film-free cotton comprehensive technology we developed can completely realize cotton planting without mulching film, and can completely solve the problem of residual film pollution and realize green cotton planting. &quot;
Yu Shuxun, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, introduced.
Xinjiang is China&#39;s most important cotton-producing area. According to statistics from the National Bureau of Statistics, Xinjiang&#39;s cotton planting area was 35 million acres in 2017, accounting for 61% of the country&#39;s cotton area.
Since the introduction of mulch film into China in 1982, the area covered with various crops in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million acres, and the annual use of mulch film is about 300,000 tons.
Among them, the cotton mulching film coverage rate reaches 100%, and cotton field mulching accounts for about 60% of the mulching film usage in Xinjiang.
The film-free cotton production was measured and the cotton output can completely achieve a yield of 320 kilograms to 350 kilograms per mu.
As the input of mulch film in Xinjiang continues to increase, the recovery rate of residual mulch film is low, the amount of residual mulch film in the soil gradually increases, and the residual mulch film causes a series of problems such as soil structural damage, which seriously affects the sustainable development of agriculture.
The residual film not only causes serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of cotton fiber.
At present, more than one-third of the cotton fields in Xinjiang have achieved mechanized harvesting.
In 2017, the area of machine-picked cotton in Xinjiang was approximately 14 million acres.
During the harvesting process of machine-picked cotton, a large amount of crumbs are collected on the surface and on the cotton plants. The crumbs mixed in the raw cotton are difficult to remove during the raw cotton processing, and cannot be completely removed during the subsequent textile processing, seriously affecting the quality of textile products. .
On September 28, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion exchange event was held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to solve the problem of mulching film pollution in cotton fields, simplify cotton planting technology, and improve cotton field efficiency, Yu Shuxun led his team to implement the &quot;China Cotton 619&quot; film-free cotton technology planting for 8 years, &quot;adding wings&quot; to the green development of Xinjiang agriculture.
Yu Shuxun introduced that through innovative new breeding ideas, a new upland cotton strain &quot;Zhongmian 619&quot; was developed that is extremely early-maturing, salt-alkali tolerant, low-temperature tolerant, and high-yielding.
&quot;&#39;Zhongmian 619&#39;, under the film-free cultivation conditions in southern Xinjiang, has achieved a series of supporting facilities such as film-free sowing machinery, improvement of sowing depth, shallow burial of dropper belts under film-free conditions, selection of suitable seeding density, and rational chemical control. measure. &quot;
At present, film-free cotton demonstration bases have been established in Aksu, Korla, Alar and other places, with a yield of 4,800 kilograms per hectare.
Growing cotton without film has achieved high yield, cost saving, environmental protection, and improved overall benefits.
Zhang Donghai, an agronomist at the Institute of Agricultural Sciences of the Third Division of the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through the research and demonstration of film-free cotton cultivation technology in the past six years, the production of film-free cotton seed cotton can fully achieve a yield of 320 kilograms to 350 kilograms per mu, or even higher.
&quot;The promotion of film-free cotton cultivation technology has great prospects. &quot;
Zhang Donghai believes that currently, film-free cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but the current economic benefits are still far behind compared with film cultivation.
&quot;The support for cotton purchase price will be conducive to future promotion. &quot;
Yu Shuxun said that in the next step, he and his team will continue to conduct in-depth research and large-scale promotion and application of film-free cotton, make the film-free cotton industry bigger and stronger, and completely solve the soil pollution problem caused by mulch films.
