The State Administration for Market Regulation recently issued the &quot;Notice on Strengthening Market Price Supervision during the Mid-Autumn Festival and National Day in 2018&quot;. The notice requires that price supervision in the housing rental and real estate fields be strengthened, and strict rectification of rent price collusion, hoarding of rental housing, and fabrication and hype to raise prices Price violations such as rent, arbitrary charging of bundled services, publishing misleading price information, and unclear price tags.
The notice clearly calls for strengthening price monitoring and early warning and paying close attention to market price dynamics.
All localities should pay close attention to the market and price changes of daily necessities such as grains, oils, meat, poultry, eggs, vegetables, milk, and salt that are heavily consumed, as well as special commodities consumed by local residents during festivals, and strengthen price monitoring, analysis, and early warning.
Once the tendencies and emerging problems of market fluctuations are discovered, timely measures can be taken to effectively resolve them.
It is necessary to strengthen supervision and inspection of the wholesale and retail links of daily necessities, increase the frequency of monitoring and supervision of places closely related to people&#39;s daily consumption, such as supermarkets and farmers&#39; markets, and urge operators to abide by the law and operate with integrity.
The notice pointed out that it is necessary to strengthen inspections in key areas to create a good holiday consumption environment; strengthen supervision of ticket prices in state-owned scenic spots; focus on investigating and punishing state-owned scenic spots that do not implement the price levels or fluctuation ranges prescribed by the government, add charging items without authorization, and set up &quot;parks within gardens&quot; in violation of regulations Tickets and other forms of disguised increases in ticket prices, high pricing and deep discounts, bundled sales, failure to clearly mark prices in accordance with regulations, failure to implement preferential measures, extra-price increases, forced collection of fees and other illegal and illegal activities.
The notice requires that price supervision of daily necessities, especially agricultural products, be strengthened.
Affected by seasonal changes, natural disasters and sudden epidemics, the prices of vegetables, pork and other necessary agricultural products have recently fluctuated in some areas.
All localities should take into account actual local conditions, effectively strengthen market price supervision of agricultural and sideline products, cooperate with relevant departments to stabilize production and market supply, and organize forces to carry out key market inspections and random inspections.
For commodities such as pork that are in tight supply and whose prices are rising rapidly, the frequency of inspections will be increased, and illegal activities such as hoarding, price gouging, and collusion in price increases will be severely investigated and dealt with.
The notice pointed out that it is necessary to strengthen price supervision in the housing rental and real estate fields.
The Mid-Autumn Festival and National Day coincide with the peak seasons for housing rentals and commercial housing sales. All localities must pay close attention to the price behavior of real estate companies, intermediary companies and housing rental-related companies, and strictly crack down on collusion in rent prices, hoarding of rental housing, fabricating and hyping false information to drive up rents, and bundling services. Price violations such as arbitrary charging, publishing misleading price information, and unclear price tags shall be strengthened to inspect hot-selling properties and real estate agents’ clearly marked prices, and the failure to implement “one set, one bid” in accordance with regulations will harm consumption. Behaviors that protect the interests of investors and disrupt market order will be investigated and punished, the real estate market environment will be purified, and an open and transparent real estate market price order will be created.
The notice mentions that all localities should effectively supervise prices in other links of the tourism industry, focus on standardizing the price order in catering, accommodation, shopping, sightseeing, entertainment, parking and other links, guide operators to do a good job of clearly marking prices and announcing charges, and seriously investigate and punish all parties. Price violations.
The notice stated that it is necessary to strengthen the inspection of transportation prices such as roads, railways, civil aviation, and water transportation, and seriously investigate and punish illegal price increases, extra-price charges, and failure to clearly mark prices in accordance with regulations.
Implement the &quot;green channel&quot; for the transportation of fresh agricultural products and the policy of exempting small passenger vehicles from tolls on major holidays.
It is necessary to innovate supervision methods and working methods, strengthen the publicity of price laws and regulations for online and offline commodity retail enterprises and e-commerce platforms, urge operators to improve price promotion plans, and investigate and deal with illegal activities such as fictitious original prices, misleading price indications, and failure to fulfill price commitments in accordance with the law. .
