The reporter learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission, and the Ministry of Commerce recently jointly issued a notice. In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, foreign investors will be allocated from resident enterprises in China. The scope of application of the policy of temporarily exempting withholding income tax for domestic direct investment has been expanded from encouraged foreign investment projects to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and fields.
This policy is effective from January 1, 2018.
The notice clarifies that direct investment by foreign investors with shared profits includes equity investments such as capital increase, new construction, and equity acquisition by foreign investors with shared profits, but does not include new investments other than qualified strategic investments. , transfer and acquire shares of listed companies.
If foreign investors can enjoy the policy of temporarily exempting withholding income tax according to regulations but have not actually enjoyed it, they can apply to retroactively enjoy the policy within three years from the date of actual payment of relevant taxes and have the tax paid refunded.
Not only that, after foreign investors enjoy the stipulated temporary exemption from withholding income tax, if the invested enterprise undergoes a reorganization that meets the conditions for special reorganization and is actually taxed according to the special reorganization, it can continue to enjoy the temporary exemption from withholding income tax. Policy treatment.
In order to ensure that the profits distributed by foreign investors are actually used for direct investment, the notice stipulates that if the profits used by foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds will be directly transferred from the account of the profit-distributing enterprise to the invested enterprise or equity. The transferor&#39;s account shall not be transferred to other accounts at home and abroad before direct investment; if the profits used by foreign investors for direct investment are paid in non-cash forms such as physical objects, marketable securities, etc., the ownership of the relevant assets shall be directly transferred from the profit-distributing enterprise to the investee. Enterprises or equity transferors shall not be held by other enterprises or individuals on their behalf or temporarily before direct investment.
The notice also requires the tax department to strengthen follow-up management in accordance with the law.
Overseas investors have enjoyed the policy of temporarily exempting withholding income tax. If they do not meet the prescribed conditions after subsequent management by the tax department, in addition to the responsibility of the profit distribution enterprise, the overseas investor will be deemed to have failed to declare and pay corporate income tax in accordance with regulations, and will be held accountable in accordance with the law. Tax liability and tax deferment period are calculated from the date of payment of relevant profits.
