Xinhua News Agency, Fuzhou, October 1 (Reporter Tai Xiaoan) On October 1, the &quot;Fujian Provincial High-speed Railway Safety Management Regulations&quot; were officially implemented.
The regulations stipulate that flying kites, balloons, sky lanterns, aircraft and other flying objects and small aircraft are prohibited within 500 meters on both sides of high-speed railway power line conductors.
It is stipulated that on the basis of the &quot;Railway Law of the People&#39;s Republic of China&quot;, &quot;Railway Safety Management Regulations&quot; and other higher-level laws, and based on the geographical and climatic characteristics of Fujian Province, supplementary provisions are made on prohibited and restricted behaviors that affect high-speed rail safety, and standardize construction, tree planting, etc. along the high-speed rail lines. conduct, further clarify the high-speed rail supervision subjects and scope of supervision, and clarify law enforcement and supervision responsibilities and legal responsibilities.
In view of the frequent strong winds along the coast of Fujian Province and the situation that light construction materials and light objects along the high-speed railway are blown into the high-speed railway, which affects safety, the regulation stipulates that the flying of kites and balloons is prohibited within 500 meters on both sides of the high-speed railway power line conductors. , sky lanterns, paramotors, aircraft and other floating objects and small aircraft.
In addition, the owners or users of light objects such as plastic greenhouses, color steel plates, and sunshade nets along the high-speed railway line, as well as low-altitude floating objects, plastic protective films and other light objects generated during the construction process, must take reinforcement and protective measures to prevent endangering the safety of the high-speed railway. .
In view of the characteristics of Fujian Province, which is located in hilly areas and has many high-speed railway tunnels, regulations require the construction of mountain ponds, reservoirs, dams, excavation of rivers, main canals, and wells, etc., within 200 meters on both sides of the center line above the high-speed railway tunnels, which may affect the tunnels. For safe behavior, the opinions of the railway construction unit or railway transportation enterprise must be sought.
At the same time, those who violate the relevant responsibilities of the &quot;Regulations&quot; will be ordered to make corrections by the public security organs; if the circumstances are serious, the unit shall be fined not less than 5,000 yuan but not more than 10,000 yuan, and the individual shall be fined not less than 200 yuan but not more than 500 yuan; if the circumstances are serious, , the unit shall be fined not less than 10,000 yuan but not more than 30,000 yuan, and the individual shall be fined not less than 500 yuan but not more than 1,000 yuan.
If losses are caused, they shall be liable for compensation in accordance with the law.
It is understood that with the rapid development of railway construction, the mileage of high-speed railways with speeds of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian Province has now reached 1,516 kilometers, realizing the implementation of bullet trains in cities. It is expected that in the next five years, railway lines with speeds of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian will Reached 2150 kilometers.
The implementation of this regulation will standardize the safety management of high-speed rail in Fujian Province, further implement the responsibilities of local government departments, coordinate railway and local forces, work together to ensure the safety of high-speed rail, and improve the safety prevention and control system of high-speed rail in Fujian Province.
