Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi delivered a speech at the Council on Foreign Relations on Friday, saying that currently, Sino-US relations have once again reached a crossroads. If the two sides can view each other actively and inclusively, expand and deepen positive cooperation, and properly manage differences and conflicts, they can open up new opportunities. Bright future.
&quot;China-US relations are our common assets and need to be taken care of by us together. &quot;
He expressed the hope that people of insight from all walks of life in both countries would take practical actions to maintain the healthy and stable development of Sino-US relations and jointly push Sino-US relations forward in the right direction.
Wang Yi also emphasized again that China will definitely embark on a development path that is different from that of traditional major powers.
This path with Chinese characteristics determines that China will not and cannot repeat the mistakes of a strong country that must seek hegemony. It also determines that China will neither become the United States, challenge the United States, nor replace the United States.
When Wang Yi delivered a speech titled &quot;Opportunity or Challenge, Partner or Rival&quot;, he said that the deep-rooted crux of the current problem is that some American friends believe that China will also become hegemonic when it becomes strong, and will even challenge and replace the United States&#39; role in the world. leadership.
&quot;This is obviously a major strategic misjudgment. &quot;
He said that this kind of self-imagined suspicion is spreading, amplifying existing contradictions, giving birth to new doubts, and making it more difficult for China and the United States to solve specific problems and encountering more resistance.
Wang Yi pointed out that China is following a path of peaceful development.
The Chinese have never had the gene for external expansion.
We believe that countries can coexist harmoniously, communicate and learn from each other.
No matter in the past, present or future, China will neither copy foreign models nor ask other countries to copy China&#39;s practices.
Earlier, when Wang Yi met with former U.S. Secretary of State Kissinger in New York, he said that cooperation between China and the U.S. would be a win-win situation, while confrontation would inevitably lead to a lose-lose situation.
China has always been committed to developing long-term, healthy and stable Sino-US relations and achieving non-conflict, non-confrontation, mutual respect and win-win cooperation.
