It is reported that hundreds of people were celebrating festivals on the beaches of Palu when the earthquake and tsunami occurred. Many people were swept away by huge waves and died.
Officials said the tsunami hit the shore at a speed of 800 kilometers per hour, destroying many buildings and infrastructure.
Thousands of homes, hospitals, shopping malls and hotels collapsed, and tsunami-induced mudslides cut off a main highway in Palu, he said.
