Guajardo said, &quot;In the next 48 hours, we will know whether we have reached a three-party agreement text or whether we have to publish the text of a two-party agreement. &quot;
Guajardo said his U.S. and Canadian counterparts &quot;specifically requested&quot; that the release of the text be delayed.
A spokesman for the Office of the United States Trade Representative (USTR) did not comment on the text of the trade agreement between the United States and Mexico and the negotiations between the United States and Canada.
Officials in the Canadian Prime Minister&#39;s Office and the Office of the Minister of Foreign Affairs did not respond to requests for comment on the counter-proposal.
