Beijing News (Reporter Ni Wei) The State Administration of Radio, Film and Television issued the &quot;Notice on Carrying out Special Rectification Work on Radio and Television Advertising&quot; on September 29, and will carry out special rectification work on radio and television advertising from now until the end of this year.
The content of the rectification includes advertisements with vulgar content, poor style and taste, and medical and health programs that broadcast problems without filing for management.
According to the notice, this special rectification work focuses on finding and rectifying nine aspects.
Specifically, they include: advertisements with orientation problems; advertisements with vulgar content, poor style and poor taste; advertisements with time-out, over-extension, and non-compliance with regulations; exaggeration, false propaganda, misleading audiences, or disguised release in the form of programs, etc. There are problematic medical, pharmaceutical, medical equipment, health food, cosmetics, beauty and other advertisements, and there are problematic medical and health programs that are broadcast without registration management; there are exaggerated and false propaganda, misleading the audience, and luring the audience to be deceived. Advertisements for investment and financial management, collectibles, etc. that have expected return on investment; advertisements that induce minors to engage in bad behavior or form bad values, harm minors’ physical and mental health; and advertisements that do not meet the regulations for the duration and frequency of public service advertisements. There are problems with requirements; there are problems with imperfect advertising broadcast management systems, lax review and inadequate implementation of responsibilities; there are advertisements with other violations of laws and regulations.
This rectification work will achieve full coverage across the country, and the rectification and standardization requirements will be fully implemented in all levels of radio and television media, each channel frequency, each program column and time period, &quot;leaving no blind spots, no dead ends, and no exceptions.&quot;
The notice requires that the radio and television administrative departments at all levels must handle all types of illegal advertisements discovered during supervision and inspection in strict accordance with the General Administration&#39;s &quot;Measures for Handling Violations by Radio and Television Broadcasting Agencies&quot;.
For serious violations, serious punishments such as admonishment talks, notification of criticism, suspension of advertising broadcasts, and suspension of frequency channel broadcasts will be given, and they will be publicly exposed to the public as appropriate.
In recent years, the State Administration of Radio, Film and Television has repeatedly stopped illegal advertising.
This year, the State Administration of Radio and Television issued a notice to publicly suspend the &quot;Zero Fruit Milk&quot;, &quot;Sara Cocktail&quot;, &quot;Bangruite Plant Anti-hair Loss Hair Lotion&quot; and other serious violations such as misleading guidance, exaggerated propaganda and misleading the audience. advertise.
The State Administration of Press, Publication, Radio, Film and Television has formulated a number of regulations and notices to regulate advertising broadcasts on radio and television.
The &quot;Notice on Further Strengthening the Management of TV Shopping Short Film Advertisements Broadcasted by Satellite TV Channels&quot; stipulates that each satellite TV channel shall not broadcast TV shopping short film advertisements between 18:00 and 24:00 every day.
When TV shopping video advertisements are broadcast at other times, hosts are not allowed to be used for promotion, &quot;hawking style&quot; exaggerated dubbing, intonations, movements, etc. are not allowed to be used for promotion, and &quot;orthopedics&quot;, &quot;shaping&quot;, &quot;fat penetration&quot;, &quot; To promote breast enhancement or weight loss products such as “Fat Loss” or in disguise, the TV shopping video advertisements shall not be broadcast more than one (time) per hour per day, and each advertisement shall not exceed 3 minutes.
The &quot;Notice on Further Strengthening the Management of Broadcasting of Radio and Television Advertisements&quot; stipulates that when TV stations insert advertisements in the middle of film and television dramas, they must strictly abide by the provisions of the General Administration&#39;s Order No. 61: 2 commercial advertisements can be inserted in each episode (45 minutes) during non-prime time , the duration of each episode shall not exceed 1 minute and 30 seconds; during prime time (19:00 to 21:00), one commercial advertisement may be inserted in each episode, and the duration shall not exceed 1 minute; when advertisements are inserted, the duration of the advertisement shall be prompted.
The notice also stipulates that radio and television broadcasting organizations must strictly examine the qualifications, certificates and other statutory materials of health information advertisements such as medical treatment, drugs, medical equipment, health food, etc., and resolutely prohibit the broadcast of sexually-related advertisements.
It is necessary to standardize the form of health information advertising, and advertisements in the form of health information special programs must not be released in disguise.
Health information special programs should focus on the introduction of scientific knowledge such as disease prevention, control and treatment, and shall not contain advertising content promoting medical treatment, drugs, medical equipment, health food, etc., and shall not testify in the names of patients, doctors, pharmacists, experts, etc.
