According to the New York Times, Iranian Foreign Minister Javad Zarif revealed in an interview on the 29th that despite the U.S. threat to impose sanctions on any country that does business with Iran, Tehran is close to reaching an agreement on crude oil sales with the European Union.
The core purpose of this agreement is to try to establish a new payment mechanism, that is, to replace U.S. dollar transactions with barter or local currency pricing.
The purpose of this approach is to bypass the United States and prevent the United States from impeding financial transfers.
At the same time, although the EU is committed to promoting the agreement, some French and British officials are also worried that if the agreement is realized, this will be the most public confrontation between the EU and the United States, which opposes the United States&#39; withdrawal from the Iran nuclear agreement.
