China News Service, Fuzhou, September 30 (Reporter Long Min) The sixth meeting of the Standing Committee of the 13th People&#39;s Congress of Fujian Province voted on the 30th to adopt the &quot;Regulations on the Promotion of Ecological Civilization Construction in Fujian Province.&quot;
“Lucid waters and lush mountains are invaluable assets” were written into Fujian Provincial legislation for the first time, running through the entire regulations and becoming an operable and enforceable provision.
Fujian is China’s first national ecological civilization experimental zone.
The person in charge of the Legislative Affairs Office of the Fujian Provincial People&#39;s Government said that a basic regulation on the construction of ecological civilization should be formed from an overall and overall perspective to solve the problem of relying solely on scattered laws, regulations, and policy documents to regulate the construction of ecological civilization, and also to formulate and issue relevant regulations and normative laws. It is very necessary and urgent for documents and measures to provide legal basis.
This regulation fully embodies the characteristics of Fujian, and transforms the mature experience and practices in the construction of ecological civilization into the form of laws and regulations for promotion and implementation: For example, the &quot;Changting Experience&quot; formed by Fujian&#39;s soil and water conservation management work can be replicated and promoted. Maintaining management experience to summarize and improve, stipulates that local people&#39;s governments at or above the county level should strengthen unified leadership over soil and water conservation work, and delineate key soil and water loss prevention areas and control areas based on water and soil loss survey results; another example is the river chief that originated in Fujian Province system, the regulations raised the river chief system and lake chief system to the legislative level, stipulating that local people&#39;s governments at all levels should fully implement the river chief system and lake chief system, and implement the main bodies, responsibilities and funds for river and lake management and protection.
The regulations stipulate that a lifelong accountability system for ecological environment damage liability shall be implemented.
Those who violate the requirements of scientific development and cause serious damage to ecological and environmental resources will be held accountable for life by the main leading cadres and relevant persons in charge.
According to reports, the &quot;Regulations on the Promotion of Ecological Civilization Construction in Fujian Province&quot; will come into effect on November 1 this year.
China and Pakistan agree to timely complete the ongoing projects of the Economic Corridor and accelerate the construction of Gwadar Port
China and Pakistan have agreed to further consolidate and expand economic relations between the two countries, the Chinese Foreign Ministry said on Sunday.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen their strategic partnership.
The two sides reiterated their &quot;commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor&quot; and &quot;opposed negative publicity against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.&quot;
Reuters quoted the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs as saying that China and Pakistan will &quot;strengthen pragmatic cooperation in the field of trade and investment and enhance Pakistan&#39;s industrial capabilities by establishing joint ventures in priority areas, transferring labor-intensive industries, and carrying out cooperation with small and medium-sized enterprises.&quot;
A press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs stated that the two sides agreed to timely complete the projects under construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor, accelerate the construction of Gwadar Port and supporting projects, focus on economic and social development, create employment and improve people&#39;s livelihood, and accelerate the development of industries, parks and agricultural fields. Cooperation.
&quot;The two sides also agreed to complete the second phase of negotiations on the China-Pakistan Free Trade Agreement as soon as possible and continue to advance the negotiations on the China-Pakistan Services Trade Agreement. &quot;
In the joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor and agreed that the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor is a win-win cooperation plan that will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region.
Both sides agreed that Gwadar Port is an important node for cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
Both sides agreed to speed up the construction of Gwadar Port and supporting projects.
China and Pakistan also expressed their opposition to negative publicity against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor in a joint statement.
The two sides agreed to establish a strategic dialogue between the foreign ministers of China and Pakistan and adjust the original strategic dialogue at the deputy foreign minister level to diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level exchanges of visits between the two militaries and exchanges between various departments and levels.
In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, China’s Ministry of Finance and other four ministries and commissions jointly announced that starting from January 1, 2018, profits distributed by foreign investors from Chinese resident enterprises for domestic direct investment will not be levied temporarily. The scope of application of the withholding income tax policy has been expanded from projects that encourage foreign investment to all projects and fields that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
A relevant notice published on the website of the Ministry of Finance stated that foreign investors must meet several conditions at the same time to temporarily exempt withholding income tax, including direct investment made by foreign investors with shared profits, including capital increase and new construction made by foreign investors with shared profits. , equity acquisition and other equity investment behaviors, but does not include new additions, transfers, and acquisitions of shares of listed companies (except for qualified strategic investments).
It also includes the profits distributed by foreign investors, which are equity investment income such as dividends and bonuses formed by the actual distribution of realized retained earnings by Chinese resident enterprises to investors.
If the profits used by foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds shall be transferred directly from the account of the profit-distributing enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and shall not be transferred to other domestic or overseas accounts before direct investment; overseas investment If the profits used for direct investment are paid in non-cash forms such as physical objects or securities, the ownership of the relevant assets is directly transferred from the profit-distributing enterprise to the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and shall not be held by other enterprises or individuals on their behalf before direct investment. Have or temporarily hold.
The notice also stated that foreign investors who actually recover direct investments that enjoy the temporary exemption of withholding income tax through equity transfers, repurchases, liquidations, etc. shall report back payment to the tax department within 7 days after actually receiving the corresponding amounts according to prescribed procedures. Deferred taxes.
In order to encourage foreign investors to continue to invest and operate in China, four ministries and commissions including the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce of China jointly issued a notice at the end of 2017. Starting from January 1, 2017, profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China will be directly For those who invest in encouraged investment projects and meet the prescribed conditions, a deferred tax policy will be implemented and withholding income tax will not be levied for the time being.
The executive meeting of the State Council of China decided last week to expand the scope of temporary exemption from withholding income tax on foreign reinvestment from encouraged foreign investment projects to all non-prohibited projects and fields, further strengthening the protection of intellectual property rights.
The reporter learned from the National Health Commission that compared with a few decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in my country has decreased, but the incidence of overweight and obesity has increased significantly.
Experts point out that the most important concept in maintaining a healthy weight is to &quot;treat the disease before it&#39;s too late&quot; and vigorously promote scientific fitness and reasonable diet.
According to the &quot;Core Information and Interpretation of Health Education for Chinese Adolescents (2018 Edition)&quot; recently released by the National Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is a reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Being overweight, obese and blindly losing weight are all bad for your health.
The health risks behind &quot;little chubby&quot; cannot be ignored.
Ding Gangqiang, director of the Institute of Nutrition and Health at the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said that overweight and obesity harm the normal growth and development of adolescents, have adverse effects on their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence, and can even lead to high blood pressure, hyperglycemia, and hyperlipidemia in children.
At the same time, overweight and obesity in adolescents are likely to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes in adulthood.
Ding Gangqiang said that the 2010-2012 nutrition and health status test of Chinese residents showed that the overweight rate of children and adolescents aged 6-17 in my country was 9.6%, and the obesity rate was 6.4%. The sum of the two is 16%.
At the same time, overweight and obesity among children and adolescents are higher in boys than in girls, and in urban areas than in rural areas. The overweight and obesity rate has increased significantly in recent decades.
How do teenagers cope with being overweight and obese?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion Research Center of the State Sports General Administration, pointed out that the main causes of obesity among adolescents are excessive caloric intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this kind of simple obesity, we should pay attention to scientific exercise and reasonable diet control.
Zhang Li pointed out that the most important concept in maintaining a healthy weight is to &quot;treat the disease before it&#39;s too late&quot;. A very important part of this is to provide comprehensive science education to schools, parents and students, popularize the dangers of overweight and obesity, and improve prevention among teenagers. consciousness.
Adolescents should have regular physical examinations, monitor growth and development indicators such as height and weight, and detect early and scientifically determine whether overweight and obesity problems occur so that timely intervention measures can be taken.
For teenagers who are already overweight and obese, Ding Gangqiang suggested that in addition to actively and scientifically arranging meals and exercise, teenagers are in a special physiological stage and should avoid using starvation or semi-starvation therapy to control and lose weight, and must not blindly take weight loss drugs.
September 28 (Reuters) - Facebook (FB.O) said on Friday that hackers stole digital login codes, giving them access to nearly 50 million user accounts, an unprecedented scale and the most serious security breach in its history.
Facebook, which has more than 2.2 billion monthly users, said it had not determined whether the attackers abused any accounts or stole personal information.
The company also has not located the location of the hackers and is not sure if they targeted specific victims.
Its preliminary analysis showed that this was a widespread attack.
CEO Zuckerberg called the incident &quot;really serious&quot; during a media conference call.
A spokesperson for the company said his account and that of chief operating officer Sheryl Sandberg were also affected.
Facebook shares fell 2.6% on Friday, dragging down Wall Street&#39;s major indexes.
U.S. lawmakers said on Friday that the attack could increase calls for data privacy legislation.
&quot;This is yet another sad piece of evidence that Congress needs to take action to protect the privacy and security of social media users,&quot; Democratic Senator Mark Warner said in a statement.
Federal Trade Commission (FTC) Commissioner Rohit Chopra said on Twitter, &quot;I want answers to Reuters&#39; reporting on this security breach.&quot;
