China News Service, Yichang, October 1 (Guo Xiaoying, Liu Min) The newly revised &quot;Three Gorges-Gezhouba Water Conservancy Project Navigation Dispatch Regulations&quot; (hereinafter referred to as the &quot;Dispatch Regulations&quot;) will be officially implemented on October 1, and the Three Gorges ship lift will After two years of trial navigation, it was officially coordinated with the ship lock.
On the first day of implementation of the new regulations, navigation in the Three Gorges-Gezhouba waters was in good order.
The Yangtze Three Gorges Navigation Administration released its first security inspection plan at 21:00 on September 30 and conducted security inspections on 160 ships. A total of 124 ships passed the security inspection.
At 14:00 on October 1, the general navigation department arranged the first gate crossing plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security inspection plan will be released at 9:00 and 21:00 every day, and the dam crossing plan will be released at 14:00 and 20:00 every day, allowing ships to flexibly arrange the dam crossing plan.
The &quot;Scheduling Regulations&quot; have added the principle of &quot;classified control&quot; for ship crossing dam dispatching. According to the functional positioning of ship locks and ship lifts, the priority of ships crossing the dam is clearly defined, and the short-line passenger ships passing the lock are adjusted to the same priority as demonstration ships and integrity ships. .
This is also the second anniversary of the trial operation of the ship lift, which is officially coordinated with the ship lock.
Large-length and wide-width demonstration ships and new energy-powered ships in the Sichuan River and Three Gorges Reservoir areas have also been prioritized for the first time.
At the same time, the &quot;Dispatch Regulations&quot; adjusted the &quot;navigation dispatch management waters&quot; from the previous 180 kilometers of waters near the dam to 541.8 kilometers of water from Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to Shishou Yangtze River Bridge, and divided it into &quot;core waters, waters near dams, controlled waters, and dispatching waters &quot;.
This will help ships choose suitable waters to wait for locks and reduce the backlog of ships waiting to be locked in the dam area.
The &quot;Scheduling Regulations&quot; also put forward integrity control measures such as canceling declarations for ships that violate regulations and delaying dam crossing for 24 hours based on the current characteristics of ships passing dams and waiting for locks.
After the Three Gorges impoundment, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, promoting the rapid development of Yangtze River shipping.
Data show that the annual cargo throughput of the Three Gorges Ship Lock and Gezhouba Ship Lock increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017 respectively.
In the two years since the Three Gorges ship lift was put into trial operation, 5,767 ships, 162,200 passengers, and 1.7128 million tons of cargo have passed through.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Administration, said that the &quot;Scheduling Regulations&quot; have a positive effect on promoting honest lock crossing management, maintaining the navigation order of the two dam hubs, alleviating the pressure on ships waiting for locks in the dam area, and improving navigation capabilities.
