Ni Yufeng, chief engineer of the Hukou Scenic Area Management Committee, told the media that this is the longest high water level in the Yellow River has lasted in the past 20 years. &quot;It has never been closed for such a long time before. In 2017, we were closed for four days during the flood season. This year it is Nearly a month. &quot;
