At present, the flow of the main stream of the Yellow River is relatively large. The flow of the upper reaches is maintained at 2,000-3,000 cubic meters per second, the flow of the middle reaches is maintained at 2,500-3,500 cubic meters per second, and the flow of the downstream rivers is maintained at 3,000 cubic meters per second.
Health centers and health stations provide influenza vaccination services especially during the National Day holiday
The Health Bureau has ordered 150,000 doses of the 2018-2019 quadrivalent influenza vaccine this year. At this stage, priority is given to high-risk individuals for free vaccination. In order to facilitate residents to receive influenza vaccines during the holidays, the health centers and health stations under the Health Bureau will specially organize the National Day holiday ( Vaccination services will be provided from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. on October 1 and 2.
In addition to the above-mentioned convenience measures, the health centers and health stations under the Health Bureau have extended the influenza vaccination service hours from Monday to Friday to 8:00 pm since the launch of the plan. As of 4:00 pm on September 30, 4,158 people have been vaccinated. The number of people vaccinated is 3,714 more than the same period last year.
Free vaccination targets include the following Macao residents: those aged 6 months to under 18 years old, those aged 50 and above, pregnant women, all patients with chronic diseases, including obese people (i.e. those with a body mass index of 30 or above), as well as institutions and nurseries , staff in kindergartens, primary schools, and secondary schools, all health workers, and Macau residents working in gaming casinos.
At the same time, for other personnel that the Health Bureau deems necessary to be vaccinated, including those in the public sector, the Health Bureau will proactively contact relevant institutions to obtain the list and then the health center will arrange vaccination.
In order to facilitate vaccinators and reduce waiting time for vaccination, the Health Bureau will send medical staff to local secondary schools, primary schools, kindergartens and nurseries from October to December this year to conduct collective vaccination for children, primary and secondary school students, teachers and staff. Get a flu vaccine; in addition, the Health Bureau will also arrange for personnel to go to residential homes for the elderly and disabled, public departments or other institutions with a large number of people for collective vaccination.
If students and young children are unable to participate in group vaccination, they can hold Macao Resident Identity Card, Health Bureau User Card, Influenza Vaccination Card (if available), student ID card, employee ID card or professional certification document starting from December 3, 2018 Get vaccinated at the vaccination station or health center of the Conte Jean General Hospital.
The Health Bureau reminds residents that people who received the 2017-2018 influenza vaccine between September 2017 and August 2018 still need to receive the new season influenza vaccine starting in September 2018, because the 2018-2019 Northern Hemisphere influenza vaccine The influenza antigen composition contained has been updated, which is targeted at seasonal influenza in the northern hemisphere in the winter of 2018-2019 and the summer of 2019.
The peak season of influenza in Macao usually occurs from January to March every year, later than in temperate regions (such as northern China and Japan). The Health Bureau calls on the elderly, children, pregnant women, obese people and chronically ill people who are more likely to develop complications after being infected with influenza. People at high risk of the disease and those who frequently come into contact with high-risk people should get vaccinated as early as possible.
