Although the global financial market continues to be turbulent, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Monday that the Exchange Fund&#39;s investment income in the third quarter of this year fell 97% year-on-year but was better than the previous quarter&#39;s performance, as overseas stocks rose under the Sino-US trade war. Foreign exchange losses also narrowed significantly.
According to the latest data from the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, the Exchange Fund recorded investment income of HK$1.6 billion from July to September 2018, significantly lower than the HK$61.8 billion in the same period last year, but better than the revised HK$100 million in the second quarter of this year.
Chan Delin, President of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, said at the Legislative Council that at the beginning of the Sino-U.S. trade war, Hong Kong and emerging market stock indexes ran counter to the U.S. stock index. It was not until the end of September and early October that the U.S. stock market indexes peaked, and market sentiment began to reverse, as investors Gradually, we realize that the trade war is also detrimental to the United States itself.
&quot;It is a good thing that market sentiment changes. If the trade war only has a unilateral impact, it will not help much to solve the problem. &quot;
But he also pointed out, &quot;If the Sino-US trade war cannot be resolved, financial market volatility will continue to rise. &quot;
In the third quarter of this year, the Exchange Fund&#39;s stock investment losses in Hong Kong narrowed 8% from the previous quarter to HK$4.7 billion, while overseas stock investment income surged 172% to HK$12.8 billion; foreign exchange losses were HK$16.2 billion, and bond income was HK$9.7 billion. , decreased by 24% and 31% respectively quarter-on-quarter, mainly reflecting the general rise of the US dollar against major currencies during the quarter and the rise of US interest rates above the 3% level in mid-September.
The Exchange Fund is mainly used to support the Hong Kong dollar.
Hong Kong has implemented a linked exchange rate system in which the Hong Kong dollar is pegged to the U.S. dollar since 1983.
Regarding Hong Kong&#39;s current financial situation, Chen Delin said that economic and asset market uncertainties have increased, and downside risks have increased. However, Hong Kong&#39;s financial system is stable, well defensive, and has sufficient earthquake resistance.
&quot;Hong Kong&#39;s international investment position is ample, with a net external asset value of US$1.4 trillion, equivalent to 4 times GDP, higher than Singapore&#39;s 2.5 times and Japan&#39;s 0.6 times. It is more than enough to cope with the economic downturn or reversal. &quot;
Recently, the Hong Kong dollar offered interest rate has continued to fall and the interest rate gap between the Hong Kong dollar and the US dollar has widened. Chen Delin pointed out that the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate once rose by more than 400 basis points on September 21. The market generally believed that it was mainly related to the increase in the Hong Kong dollar offered interest rate. Subsequently, the Hong Kong dollar against the US dollar was around 7.80-7.84. HIBOR has continued to fall recently, and the interest rate differential with the U.S. dollar has widened, which may attract an increase in arbitrage activities of selling Hong Kong dollars and buying U.S. dollars, making the chance of Hong Kong dollars triggering the weak-side convertibility guarantee greater than before.
However, he believes that as the interest rate hike cycle of Hong Kong banks begins and the normalization of Hong Kong dollar interest rates is in progress, the situation of Hong Kong dollar interest rates being lower than US dollar interest rates will change in the future.
&quot;The trend of Hong Kong dollar interest rates and US dollar interest rates will become more consistent. Everyone must manage risks more carefully and be prepared to cope with market fluctuations. &quot;
As Hong Kong dollar funds are abundant, Hong Kong dollar interest rates fell further. The three-month interest rate fell 0.9% to 2.08179% on Monday, and the interest rate difference with the U.S. dollar widened from 46 basis points to 51 basis points. The one-month interest rate hit a five-month low, with the U.S. dollar interest rate widening to 51 basis points. The difference widened from 120 basis points to 127 basis points.
From May to mid-September, the spot exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was close to 7.85 per US dollar most of the time.
During this period, due to factors such as interest arbitrage activities and the outflow of some proceeds from the IPO into Hong Kong dollars after the completion of large-scale IPOs, the weak-side convertibility guarantee was triggered multiple times in May and August after being triggered for the first time in April.
The Hong Kong Monetary Authority purchases Hong Kong dollars and sells U.S. dollars at the level of 7.85 in accordance with the linked exchange rate system to maintain the stability of the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate.
The HKMA purchased a total of approximately HK$52.1 billion under the weak-side convertibility guarantee mechanism in May and August.
Are there any benefits to foreigners under the new personal income tax law?
Relevant officials from the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation responded to reporters&#39; questions on the 30th and stated that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas persons, including persons from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, when implementing the new personal income tax law.
