Will there be any preferential arrangements for foreigners, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, when the law is implemented in the next step?
The person in charge responded that the current Implementation Regulations of the Personal Income Tax Law have special preferential provisions on the tax payment of overseas persons. Individuals who do not have a residence in China but have lived for more than one year and less than five years, their income derived from outside China can only be paid by China. The portion paid by domestic entities or individuals shall be subject to personal income tax.
The person in charge stated that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas persons, including persons from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, when implementing the new personal income tax law.
There is no &quot;threshold&quot; for confinement centers: quality certification promotes quality improvement.
With the boost of the &quot;two-child economy&quot; and the prosperity of the maternal and infant market, confinement centers of various grades have emerged in various places from Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou to third- and fourth-tier cities.
The currently popular postpartum care centers meet the consumer needs of the masses, with fees ranging from tens of thousands to hundreds of thousands of yuan. However, they are also in an embarrassing situation. So far, this institution has no threshold and there is still a gap in supervision.
The State Administration for Market Regulation recently launched a series of national &quot;Quality Month&quot; activities in 2018. The reporter came to a five-star confinement center in Tianjin to explore the maternal and infant care service certification experience.
General confinement centers provide services such as newborn care, nutritious meals, and postpartum repair and shaping.
In this confinement center, the reporter saw that nurses checked the breastfeeding status of newborns every day, and professional nurses provided detailed care services such as bathing and touching newborns.
At the same time, in order to meet the needs of new mothers, we provide services such as wound care in the early stage of confinement, body care in the middle and late stages of confinement, and TCM treatment and beauty care programs to help mothers regain their slim figure.
A new mother who lives there told reporters that she only booked this confinement center eight months in advance.
The services of confinement clubs directly affect the comfort level and physical recovery of mothers during confinement. Some small confinement clubs can only provide some simple confinement services, with non-standard disinfection and hygiene, easy cross-infection, and single diet. Unscientific and other hidden dangers.
The person in charge of this confinement center said that they are the only five-star confinement center in Tianjin that has obtained B-level service certification.
&quot;Although some customers did not understand the meaning of B-level certification at first, passing the certification forces companies to strictly standardize process management, which benefits customers and is of great significance to the long-term development of the company.&quot; He said.
Pan Lifen, deputy director of the Certification and Supervision Department of the State Administration for Market Regulation, said that service certification is a new certification system based on customer perception, focusing on organizational quality management and satisfaction of service characteristics. It is an important part of the national quality infrastructure and plays an important role in improving quality services. It plays a positive role in increasing the proportion of supply and enhancing the international competitiveness of China&#39;s services.
Our country started in 2004. After more than 10 years of development, service certification projects have experienced a process of gradual development from scratch, such as financial services certification, maternal and infant care service certification, commodity after-sales service certification, e-commerce service certification, etc. A number of influential service certifications such as health care service certification.
According to statistics from the State Administration for Market Regulation, there are currently more than 130 service certification institutions in my country, with more than 2,000 service certification personnel and nearly 8,000 valid certification certificates.
Pan Lifen said that it is necessary to further guide and promote the development of service certification, gradually expand the coverage of service certification in health, education, sports, finance, e-commerce and other fields, and promote supply-side reform and quality improvement in the service industry.
Reuters Hong Kong, November 5 - Hong Kong property prices have fallen for two consecutive months after peaking. Hong Kong Monetary Authority President Delin Chan said on Monday that it still takes time to observe whether the property market has entered a downward cycle. If confirmed, it can be considered to gradually relax at an appropriate time. Tightening policy with countercyclical measures.
Chen Delin also pointed out that if property prices fall back, the first people to be affected will be those who bought properties during the peak period of the property market. However, it is expected that the chance of property prices falling sharply and people selling their properties at significant price cuts like the one experienced during the Asian financial crisis in 1997 is much lower. .
When Chan Delin led a number of senior HKMA officials to attend a briefing at the Legislative Council, he said that if it is confirmed that the property market has entered a downward cycle, measures can be relaxed one after another as appropriate.
&quot;But we have only seen a few weeks of data now, so it is still too early to relax. We still need more time to see whether the property market has entered a downward cycle. &quot;
Since October 2009, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority has launched eight rounds of countercyclical measures to significantly tighten mortgages for various properties, including lowering mortgage ratios and requiring mortgage applicants to pass rigorous stress tests, in order to improve bank risk management and Earthquake resistance.
As Hong Kong officially entered the interest rate hike cycle, the private residential property price index in Hong Kong peaked and fell for two consecutive months from August to September. The monthly decline in September expanded to 1.44%.
However, the cumulative increase in the first three quarters of this year still reached 10.2%.
According to data from the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, household financial conditions, which measure Hong Kong&#39;s resilience to financial risks, remain healthy. In the second quarter of this year, the proportion of owner-occupied households in Hong Kong without mortgages reached 66%, compared with the 2009-11 average of 60%. High; the average loan-to-value ratio of newly approved mortgages and the payment-to-income ratio of newly approved mortgages were 47% and 34% respectively, which were significantly improved from 64% and 41% respectively in 2009-11.
However, Chen Delin said that high earthquake resistance does not mean that people who have purchased homes will not be harmed by the economic downturn, because property valuations will fall, and those who buy properties during the peak period will bear the brunt.
Although the Hong Kong Monetary Authority has tightened bank lending to mortgage lenders, homebuyers can also obtain high-percentage mortgage loans through mortgage insurance or mortgage loans provided by developers.
Chen Delin said that currently, together with the mortgage loans provided to developers, the borrower&#39;s mortgage ratio can reach 85-90%. If the property price drops by 10%, negative equity will appear (that is, the market value of the property drops below the total outstanding mortgage loan). s level) .
However, Ruan Guoheng, deputy chief executive of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, pointed out that the authority estimates that the total number of high-factor mortgages provided by developers only accounts for 2-2.5% of the total bank mortgages, which is still a low proportion.
At the peak of negative equity in Hong Kong in 2003, the number of negative equity cases exceeded 100,000, accounting for 22% of the proportion of mortgage holders.
As of the third quarter of this year, Hong Kong has recorded zero negative assets for seven consecutive quarters.
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, October 1 (Liu Hongxia, Ma Rui) E-commerce retail export companies will usher in another wave of tax benefits on October 1, involving value-added tax, consumption tax exemptions, etc.
