Lawyers carry an ax to court?
The news was indeed exciting at first glance, and it also caused a stir in legal circles.
Fujian Quanzhou Sino-French Law Firm subsequently fined the lawyer involved 500 yuan and recommended in writing that the Quanzhou Lawyers Association conduct an investigation.
According to the Beijing News, the Quanzhou Lawyers Association recently issued an official notice stating that the actions of the two lawyers did not involve any violation of laws or regulations and would not be punished in accordance with the law.
According to various reports, the Quanzhou Lawyers Association’s handling was not to defend shortcomings or engage in confrontation, but was approved by the Quanzhou Intermediate People’s Court.
An incident that might have caused tension within the legal community was finally resolved appropriately.
The reversal of the matter stems from a more complete restoration of the truth: the ax carried by the lawyer involved was of the same style and model as the defendant&#39;s murder weapon, but it was not sharpened. It was only used as auxiliary evidence in the process of evidence and cross-examination, and there was no intimidation or &quot;endangerment&quot;. court security&quot; subjective intention.
There are four very important details that need to be paid attention to when judging whether the behavior of the lawyer involved is illegal: First, the local court only showed photos of the ax in two previous sessions. From a defense perspective, it is necessary to show the original ax; Secondly, the ax was purchased only one hour before the trial. It was not because the lawyer was unwilling to seek the judge’s consent, but objectively he was unable to contact the judge; thirdly, the entire ax was not used excessively or improperly; fourthly, the incident involved The lawyer immediately publicly admitted his mistake and expressed his apology to the court.
Based on these circumstances, it can be seen that the lawyer involved &quot;bringing an ax to court&quot; has nothing to do with evil, but just to defend himself.
After clarifying the entire facts, the Quanzhou Lawyers Association did not go along with the situation, but withstood the pressure and made a decision not to impose punishment.
And this decision can also stand the test of facts and law.
As for bringing an ax, which is a regulated knife, to the court without the court&#39;s permission, it is indeed easy to cause uneasiness and misunderstanding.
Out of safety and prudence considerations, the Quanzhou Intermediate People’s Court’s previous fines and judicial recommendations are understandable.
In order to maintain the dignity of lawyers and prevent individual courts from making things difficult for lawyers, the Supreme Court issued the &quot;People&#39;s Court Judicial Police Safety Inspection Rules&quot; in 2014, establishing the principle that lawyers do not need to undergo personal safety inspections when appearing in court.
Since the promulgation of the rules, lawyers have set an example and few incidents have occurred that endanger court safety due to security loopholes.
In rare cases like Quanzhou, misunderstandings are not difficult to eliminate as long as communication is conducted in a spirit of mutual respect and understanding.
As the self-regulatory organization of the lawyer profession, the Lawyers Association has the dual mission of punishing illegal acts and ensuring legality.
In the past, individual bar associations were criticized for focusing on punishment and failing to provide protection.
The decision of the Quanzhou Lawyers Association is worthy of praise in terms of both process and results, and has set an example for more lawyers associations to correctly perform their duties.
Starting from October 1st, what personal tax benefits will affect our pockets?
Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, October 1 (Reporter Sang Tong) The new Personal Income Tax Law will come into effect on January 1, 2019. In order to allow the broad masses of the people to enjoy the tax reduction dividends as soon as possible, starting from October 1, tax payment will be first A person’s actual salary income will be deducted based on the monthly threshold of 5,000 yuan, and the new tax rate schedule will apply.
With the implementation of the New Deal, what benefits will affect people&#39;s pocketbooks?
Benefit 1: Significant tax reduction on wages and salaries
Taxpayers who receive wages and salaries after October 1 can deduct a basic deduction of 5,000 yuan per month and apply the new tax rate schedule. Most taxpayers have varying degrees of tax reductions, especially those with low and middle incomes. To be obvious.
According to the tax reduction situation table for different income groups, people with monthly incomes of 8,000 yuan, 10,000 yuan, 20,000 yuan, and 50,000 yuan after deducting the &quot;three insurances and one fund&quot; will have tax payables of 90 yuan and 290 yuan respectively after the tax reform. , 1,590 yuan, and 9,090 yuan. Compared with the monthly starting point of 3,500 yuan, the corresponding tax reduction ratios are 73.9%, 61.1%, 49.0%, and 18.8% respectively.
It is worth noting that due to holidays, the new basic deduction and tax rate schedules can be applied to the wages paid by each unit in accordance with the law at the end of September that should have been paid in October.
To this end, the withholding client software promoted and used by the tax department has provided the corresponding tax calculation function, but the corresponding taxes still need to be declared and paid within the statutory reporting period.
Benefit 2: The gap between low tax brackets has been significantly widened
In addition to raising the threshold, a new tax rate schedule will apply from October 1.
The seven tax rates for wages and salary income this time are the same as before, but the gap between tax rates has changed significantly. The gap between the three low tax brackets of 3%, 10% and 20% has been significantly expanded, and the gap between the 25% tax bracket has been significantly expanded. The gap has narrowed, while the gap between the three higher tax brackets of 30%, 35% and 45% remains unchanged.
It is worth noting that the tax law also adjusts the tax rates for various levels of income from production and operations, with the lower limit of the highest 35% tax rate raised from 100,000 yuan to 500,000 yuan.
This means that individual businesses and sole proprietorships and partnerships will benefit from the tax reform.
&quot;Judging from the previous calculations of personal tax reductions for Shanghai taxpayers, the majority of taxpayers will fully feel the dividends of the personal tax reform, especially the tax reductions for middle- and low-income groups. &quot;
Lan Min, head of the Personal Income Tax Division of the Shanghai Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, said.
Benefit 3: Tax services are more convenient and optimized
Since the promulgation of the new personal income tax law, the Shanghai tax department has launched a series of comprehensive and extensive tax publicity actions.
On the one hand, &quot;one-on-one, point-to-point&quot; policy guidance is provided to key tax sources and key enterprises.
The Pudong New Area Taxation Bureau has successively visited large enterprises such as Apple Trading (Shanghai) Co., Ltd., Alipay (China) Network Technology Co., Ltd., and Red Star Macalline Home Furnishing Group Co., Ltd. These enterprises have a large number of employees and a heavy workload of withholding and payment. , the tax amount is large, the tax department takes the initiative to provide guidance and answer questions; the Xuhui District Taxation Bureau visited the large-scale labor service companies in the region, such as Zhongzhi Financial Consulting Co., Ltd. and Zhongzhi Shanghai Economic and Technical Cooperation Company, to promptly collect concerns from enterprises and respond to their demands. , to solve corporate difficulties.
On the other hand, we will promote “all-round, multi-dimensional and three-dimensional” tax policies to the general public taxpayers.
Use the Shanghai Taxation official website, WeChat public accounts, Weibo and other channels to push policy hot spots in a timely manner to ensure that policy publicity is in place.
At the same time, starting from September 28, the Shanghai Taxation WeChat public account has been launched on the 12366 intelligent consulting platform to carry out &quot;targeted&quot; intelligent integrated individual tax reform publicity services through &quot;artificial + intelligent&quot; tax service consultation.
