The trilateral trade agreement reached by the United States, Canada and Mexico will bring new opportunities to 500 million people.
According to foreign media reports, a joint statement by Canadian Foreign Minister Freeland and U.S. Trade Representative Lighthizer published on the Canadian government website stated that the United States, Canada and Mexico have reached a trilateral trade agreement, which will be called the &quot;USMCA&quot; (U.S.-Mexico-Canada) Three-nation Agreement).
