The Ministry of Finance implements a trial exemption of value-added tax and consumption tax on cross-border e-commerce
The notice pointed out that for e-commerce export enterprises in the comprehensive pilot zone that export goods that have not obtained valid purchase certificates and meet relevant conditions, the value-added tax and consumption tax exemption policy will be implemented on a trial basis.
(1) E-commerce export enterprises register in the comprehensive pilot area and register the date of export, name of goods, unit of measurement, quantity, unit price, and amount on the cross-border e-commerce online comprehensive service platform at the place of registration.
(2) Export goods must go through e-commerce export declaration procedures through the customs where the comprehensive pilot area is located.
(3) The exported goods are not goods for which the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation have explicitly canceled export tax refunds (exemptions) in accordance with the decisions of the State Council.
It is reported that the above notice will be implemented from October 1, 2018, and the specific date shall be based on the export date stated in the export commodity declaration list.
The fifth &quot;Disability Voice Month&quot; has arrived to focus on the issue of sex education for disabled teenagers-China News
In recent years, the topic of sex education for Chinese teenagers has been widely discussed, but the challenge of sex education for teenagers with disabilities is still arduous.
Recently, a seminar on challenges and practical strategies for comprehensive sexuality education for people with disabilities was held in Beijing.
How to provide sex education to children and young people with disabilities has become an important topic in this seminar.
The &quot;Report on Sex-Related Knowledge, Attitudes and Behaviors of China&#39;s Disabled Children and Youth&quot; released at the meeting showed that the proportion of disabled children experiencing sexual harassment and sexual assault is higher than that of healthy children.
For children and teenagers with disabilities, the society pays more attention to &quot;sexual protection&quot;.
This seminar aims to discuss the promotion of comprehensive sex education for children and adolescents with disabilities in China from three aspects: family support, school education, and institutional services, and provide support for children and adolescents with disabilities from the source, so that they can enjoy love freely like others. s right.
Experts believe that the Chinese public&#39;s understanding of disabled people has always been at a level that is not deep enough.
Affected by traditional concepts and other factors, China&#39;s comprehensive sex education for people with disabilities, especially children and adolescents with disabilities, is not in-depth enough.
However, in recent years, with the support of UNESCO and public welfare individuals, the practice and implementation of sexual and reproductive health education for the full-cycle comprehensive development of people with disabilities in China have made gratifying developments.
The &quot;Report&quot; shows that although children and young people with visual impairments, hearing impairments, intellectual disabilities, and physical disabilities have more difficulties than the average person in acquiring sexual knowledge and understanding intimate relationships, they have generally become more convenient and enriched.
The &quot;Seminar on Comprehensive Sexuality Education Challenges and Practical Strategies for People with Disabilities&quot; was hosted by the Shanghai Humane Charity Foundation and jointly supported by the UNESCO Representative Office in China, the Beijing Representative Office of the International Alliance for Disabled Persons (France), and the United Nations Population Fund Representative Office in China. It aims to jointly explore the practice and implementation path of sexual and reproductive health education for the full-cycle comprehensive development of people with disabilities under the background of the Healthy China strategy, and promote policy makers, educators, researchers, social service organizations, Parent representatives and other stakeholders understand the international policy of comprehensive sexuality education and the health rights of children and youth with disabilities; conduct extensive exchanges on sexuality education practices, strategies, challenges and resources for children and youth with disabilities in China, and discuss how to provide children with disabilities with disabilities in the future Jinghe youth conduct comprehensive sexuality education discussions and develop a blueprint to form a support network.
Reuters Beijing, September 30 - The People&#39;s Bank of China released data on scheduled short-term net outflows of foreign currency assets on Sunday, which showed that as of the end of August this year, the central bank&#39;s short positions in foreign currency forward contracts and futures contracts against local currencies had been zero for 12 consecutive months, and there were still no long positions that month. position.
Previous data from the central bank showed that as of the end of August last year, the central bank held a total of US$6.044 billion in short positions in forward and futures contracts of foreign currencies against local currencies, unchanged for the fourth consecutive month; short positions denominated in SDR (Special Drawing Rights) The scale is 4.276 billion SDR.
Since then, the central bank’s short forward FX position has been at zero.
The central bank first released this data at the end of March 2016; the data showed that at the end of February 2016, the central bank&#39;s long positions in foreign currency forward contracts and futures contracts against local currencies were US$2.438 billion and short positions were US$28.9 billion.
September data released at the end of October of the same year showed for the first time a net increase in short positions of US$16.401 billion to US$45.301 billion.
The central bank has previously stated that the forward and futures short positions of foreign currencies against local currencies mainly reflect the foreign exchange forward operations carried out by the central bank with commercial banks to meet the hedging needs of enterprises’ foreign currency liabilities, and that it will continue to provide forward hedging based on the principle of actual demand. products, the central bank&#39;s forward operations will have a small impact on the future size of foreign exchange reserves.
On the evening of September 20 this year, Qiao, a junior student in Zhengzhou, took the K158 train to Hebi.
An old man on the train bought a ticket without a seat, but took her seat: &quot;Shoot, snap, snap.&quot;
After a two-hour journey, the train conductor tried to persuade him for an hour, but it still had no effect.
Finally, a male passenger in the same carriage couldn&#39;t stand it anymore and pulled the uncle up.
Judging from public opinion, although most of the final results are that the seat tyrants are condemned by the public, administratively punished by the public security department, or even included in the integrity blacklist, the public still feels that there is no &quot;relief of hatred&quot;: Why can&#39;t the seat tyrants be punished on the spot?
Why can&#39;t their immoral or even illegal behavior be stopped on the spot, but punished after the fact?
As for the unreasonable behavior of the &quot;big man in the seat&quot;, why was it just a male passenger who dragged him up because he saw an injustice on the road?
The main reason is that only long-distance trains are equipped with police officers, and short-distance trains generally do not have police officers. Even if there are police officers, the police are more concerned about the possible rogue reaction of the person occupying the seat and do not take measures to forcibly remove the passengers.
Frequent seat tying incidents have made people realize that the tyrants must be forcibly removed on the spot or even punished in order to have a deterrent effect.
This requires that our train police officers must dare to take strong and timely measures, and trains without police officers should be equipped with police officers as soon as possible to prevent and crack down on illegal activities in a timely manner.
On October 1, the first day of the National Day holiday, there was a sharp increase in traffic heading toward Songpan, Mao County, via Beichuan Qiang Autonomous County, Sichuan.
At about 13:00, the Beichuan traffic police received a call for help, saying that his family had a traffic accident in Songpan and was urgently sent to Mianyang for treatment due to limited local medical conditions.
It happens that one-way traffic control is implemented on Huanhu Road in Tangjiashan Barrier Lake, Beichuan, and I would like to ask the traffic police to allow the 120 ambulance to pass.
After receiving the call for help, the police on duty quickly reported the situation to the brigade. After briefly understanding the situation, the brigade captain Huang Xuemin immediately arranged for the police on duty at the control point to contact the caller and requested that all efforts be made to escort him.
&quot;There were more than a thousand vehicles entering the controlled road section at that time. After contacting the 120 ambulance, the estimated arrival time in Beichuan was around 15:00, and we immediately made arrangements and deployments. &quot;
Da Wei, leader of the Yuli Squadron of the Beichuan Traffic Police, said that the ambulance needed to detour from the Tangjiashan Barrier Lake Huanhu Road, and the road was steep and narrow. In order to prevent vehicles that had entered this section of the road from driving in double rows, the traffic police arrived an hour in advance. Sectional control is implemented for vehicles at the beginning, middle and end of the road, and all passing drivers are reminded to move to one side of the road to avoid missing vehicles for emergency vehicles.
Subsequently, the police from the Leigu Squadron also temporarily stopped vehicles from entering the controlled road section and lined up to give way to the approaching 120 ambulance.
At about 15:00, an ambulance with a Sichuan U license plate drove into Beichuan. The Beichuan traffic police sent a police car to clear the way and escort the ambulance into the controlled road section in the opposite direction.
It is understood that there are places on Huanhu Road that only one vehicle can pass through. The police temporarily controlled these places in advance to ensure that the 120 ambulance passed smoothly.
When arriving at Shilibei Village in Xuanping Township, there was a section of road that could not be given way, so the traffic police contacted the two village committees in advance, borrowed the village road to detour, and prohibited the entry of public vehicles.
&quot;It only took 40 minutes from the time Beichuan traffic police received the 120 ambulance to the time it entered the normal road of Provincial Highway 302. &quot;
Dawei said that under normal circumstances, the entire passage would take 4 hours.
&quot;This arrangement successfully bought valuable treatment time for the patient. &quot;
It is reported that at 17:20, critically ill patients were promptly sent to Mianyang for treatment.
