Yesterday morning at 8:05, two pickpocket suspects were caught while stealing from Yongdingmen Station to Zhushikou Station on the No. 20 bus.
Two pickpocketing men cut open the passenger&#39;s coat pockets and stole 800 yuan in cash, which was caught by the police who were already waiting nearby.
This is the first pickpocketing case cracked by Beijing police during the National Day holiday.
At around 5 o&#39;clock yesterday morning, anti-pocket investigators from the Beijing Public Security Mobile Investigation Corps arrived at their predetermined location.
According to past experience, places with concentrated crowds, bus hubs, bus and subway lines, including people watching the flag-raising in Tiananmen Square, are the key areas for their work.
In the crowd, plainclothes police officers calmly observed the passing crowds.
At around 7 a.m., investigators who were on guard at the bus station discovered two suspicious men following a male passenger onto the No. 20 bus from Yongdingmen Station.
In the car, two suspicious men, one on the left and one on the right, sandwiched the male passenger. One of them tried to cover the other.
But they didn&#39;t know that their every move had already fallen into the eyes of the plainclothes policemen who were observing.
&quot;Catch thieves and seize stolen goods&quot;, plainclothes policemen pay attention to the heat when arresting people. While waiting for the men to start stealing, the policemen stared intently at the men who were about to pickpocket. They were caught by investigators after they succeeded in pickpocketing.
A Beijing Morning News reporter saw that the police seized 800 yuan in cash from the theft suspect.
&quot;They took the money from the passengers&#39; clothes pockets. &quot;
The policeman pointed to a torn coat pocket and said: &quot;They cut this open and stole 800 yuan from a visitor to Beijing. When we caught them, the money had just been put into their own pockets. &quot;
The reporter learned that in order to catch the two men, the plainclothes police followed them for an hour and finally captured them while committing the crime.
Two suspects are currently under police review.
The plainclothes policeman told reporters that the question of who is suspicious in the crowd is very simple for the policeman.
&quot;If you catch a lot of thieves, you will find that their eyes and demeanor are different from ordinary passengers. In addition to staring at people&#39;s pockets and backpacks, they also like to sneak into the crowd instead of avoiding people. &quot;
The police also told reporters that suspects often have no purpose in waiting for the bus. They like to wander around the station and only follow the target of pickpocketing and get on the bus.
&quot;These are all words of experience. If you work in plain clothes for a long time, you will naturally know. &quot;
In addition, the police also reminded that &quot;the pockets of outerwear are the most convenient for storing things and are also the most likely to be stolen.&quot;
Please pay attention to your belongings while traveling and riding to prevent them from being stolen.
