As it is estimated that there are still people who fell into the water and are trapped at sea, relevant search and rescue operations are still continuing.
The Aegean Sea was once the preferred route for illegal immigrants to smuggle into mainland Europe via Turkey.
After Turkey controlled it in accordance with the agreement signed with the European Union in March 2016, the number of people smuggling through this channel has been greatly reduced.
But since this year, the number of illegal immigrants on this channel has rebounded.
According to the Nobel Prize official website, at 11:30 noon local time on the 1st in Stockholm, Sweden, American immunologist James Allison and Japanese immunologist Tasuku Honjo won the 2018 Nobel Prize for their discovery of cancer therapies that inhibit negative immune regulation. Prize in Physiology or Medicine.
According to Japanese media reports, Honjo is the 26th Japanese to win the Nobel Prize and the fifth Japanese to win the Physiology or Medicine Prize. The 76-year-old Honjo has made significant contributions to the creation of new drugs for the treatment of cancer. I learned the news that I had won the award in my own laboratory.
It is reported that Tasuku Honjo was born on January 27, 1942. He is a Japanese doctor and medical scientist, a foreign academician of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States, a member of the Japanese Academy of Sciences, and currently a visiting professor at Kyoto University.
Tasuku Honjo discovered the T cell inhibitory receptor PD-1 in 1992 and pioneered cancer immunotherapy in 2013. His achievements ranked first among the top ten scientific breakthroughs of the year in Science.
On September 21, 2016, Tasuku Honjo was selected for that year’s Citation Laureate list, and was hailed as “one of the Japanese closest to the Nobel Prize.”
Chinese tourists were beaten at Thai airport: the attacker was fired and the airport president was dismissed.
China News Service, September 30 (Xinhua) According to Thailand Headline News Network, recently, a video of a Chinese citizen being beaten at Don Mueang Airport in Bangkok has attracted widespread attention.
At 2 pm local time on the 29th, Surinwat, President of Don Mueang Airport of the Airports Company of Thailand, explained the incident of airport security beating tourists and expressed his deep apology.
On the other hand, it is reported that Thailand’s Deputy Prime Minister Prayit attaches great importance to this matter and has ordered the dismissal of the airport staff responsible for the incident and the removal of the president of Don Mueang Airport for investigation.
The person in charge of the Airport Authority said that at that time, the Chinese tourist was dissatisfied with being refused entry and was unwilling to obey the management and stay in the deportation restricted area, so he had a pushing and physical conflict with the security personnel.
Currently, the Airport Authority has suspended the security guard.
This incident has had an impact on Thailand&#39;s tourism image. Don Mueang Airport deeply apologizes for the incident. In order to try its best to make up for the losses, the next step of the airport will be to convey its deep apology to the Chinese tourist who was attacked through the Chinese Embassy.
Finally, the airport president Surinwa said: Chinese tourists are still welcome to travel to Thailand. Now they have provided more help and convenience to Chinese tourists entering Thailand, including opening a special courtesy channel for Chinese passports when entering Thailand. Among them, Suvarnabhumi Airport 18 are open, 21 are open at Don Mueang Airport, 18 are open at Phuket Airport; 8 are open at Chiang Mai Airport; 10 are open for Chinese tourists at Hat Yai Airport.
Thailand Headline News Network learned from the newly appointed Director-General of the National Immigration Bureau of Thailand and the former Deputy Director of the Thailand Tourism Police, Major General Surachi, that Thailand’s Deputy Prime Minister Prayat attaches great importance to this matter and has ordered the dismissal of the airport staff responsible for the incident, and has also imposed sanctions on Don Mueang. The airport president was dismissed and investigated.
According to our newspaper (intern reporter Li Qiyao), in recent years, incidents of substandard plastic runways on campuses have occurred in many places.
To this end, the Ministry of Education issued a notice requiring primary and secondary school synthetic surface sports venues delivered for use after November 1 this year to comply with the new national standards.
The mandatory national standard &quot;Synthetic Material Surface Sports Grounds for Primary and Secondary Schools&quot; was organized by the Ministry of Education, and 26 scientific research institutes and testing institutions participated in the drafting. It has been revised for more than two years, during which more than 100 expert meetings were organized for demonstration, and Nationwide on-site inspections and sampling inspections have collected countless verification experiments on the products of hundreds of companies on the market.
The reporter compared the old national standard in 2005 and found that the new national standard not only changed from &quot;national recommended standard&quot; to &quot;national mandatory standard&quot;, but also added many contents, including thickness requirements, physical properties, aging resistance, inorganic filler content requirements, anti-skid glue Requirements for polymer content in granules, limits of harmful substances in finished surface layers, limits of harmful substances in non-solid and solid raw materials, etc.
It is particularly worth mentioning that the new national standard limits the harmful substances that may be produced during the construction of campus plastic runways, increasing from the original 7 items to 18 items, and sets limits for volatile organic compounds on the completed runways in accordance with home decoration standards. stipulated.
For example, the &quot;Limits and Odor Requirements for Hazardous Substances in Cast-in-Situ and Prefabricated Surface Finished Products&quot; clearly stipulates the release amount of hazardous substances, requiring that total volatile organic compounds shall not be higher than 5 mg/cubic meter, and formaldehyde shall not be higher than 0.4 mg. / cubic meter, carbon disulfide shall not be higher than 7 mg/cubic meter, benzene shall not be higher than 0.1 mg/cubic meter, and the odor level shall not be higher than level 3.
The new national standard also provides detailed provisions on sampling requirements, inspection rules, and judgment rules for plastic runways in primary and secondary school campuses.
In addition, campus artificial turf has also been included in the mandatory testing scope of national standards for the first time.
In the near future, various localities will carry out special work arrangements for the implementation of the new national standards, and report the implementation status of the new national standards to the Department of Physical Health and Art Education of the Ministry of Education within the year.
China News Service Client, Chengdu, September 30 (Wang Yu) On the afternoon of the 30th, the &quot;National Table Tennis Civil War&quot; was staged at the 2018 Women&#39;s Table Tennis World Cup finals.
In the end, Grand Slam winner Ding Ning defeated her teammate Zhu Yuling 4:0 at home and won the Women&#39;s Table Tennis World Cup again after four years. This was also the 21st time that Chinese women&#39;s table tennis won the championship.
Ding Ning and Zhu Yuling are both teammates and friends, and both sides are quite familiar with each other&#39;s techniques and tactics.
Whether it is preparing for a game or warming up before a game, both sides are inseparable.
Entering the finals, the two unanimously stated that they had completed the competition tasks.
But the battle between Ding Ning and Zhu Yuling in the game was like a flash of sword.
In the first game, Ding Ning, who has more experience in competitions, started with a 3:1 lead. Then Zhu Yuling used Ding Ning&#39;s mistakes to tie the score at 3.
Zhu Yuling then began to make more mistakes in her offense. Ding Ning seized the opportunity and scored 3 points in a row to lead 9:5, and took the lead in getting the game point at 10:6.
Although Zhu Yuling chased for 3 points in a row, Ding Ning still used her serve to win the first game 11:9.
In the second game, Zhu Yuling&#39;s mistakes were still high, and Ding Ning took advantage of the stalemate to lead 6:1.
After falling behind 2:7, Zhu Yuling relied on a change of rhythm to score 2 points in a row, and then used her offense to chase the score to 8:9.
At the critical moment, Ding Ning scored 2 points in a row to win another game 11:8.
In the third game, the two started tight and tied at 3:3.
Ding Ning then made more mistakes in the offense and lost 3 points in a row, but she then used her sharp offense to score 3 points in a row to tie the score at 6.
Zhu Yuling scored 2 points in a row to once again establish an advantage and took the lead in getting the game point at 10:8.
However, Ding Ning attacked extremely fiercely, scoring 4 points in a row and then won the third game 12:10.
In the fourth game, Zhu Yuling started with a 4:2 lead.
But after that, Ding Ning showed a strong offensive state, scoring 4 points in a row before stopping Zhu Yuling.
After returning from the timeout, Zhu Yuling regained some form and gradually tied the score to 8:8.
At the critical moment, Ding Ning showed no mercy and scored 2 points in a row to get the match point.
As Zhu Yuling&#39;s return ball went out of bounds, Ding Ning swept the opponent 4:0 and won the championship.
Last month, Ding Ning won the Bulgarian Open, ending her 14-month championship drought. This time she came to Chengdu. Although she said before the game that she did not set a goal for this competition, in In the semi-finals that ended in the morning, Ding Ning said that he had completed his task.
In the end, Ding Ning defeated her teammate Zhu Yuling and won her third World Cup championship. She expressed satisfaction with her performance: &quot;A championship is important to every athlete.
I didn&#39;t think about this before the game. I just said that I would fight every game. I was very satisfied with my performance in the final. &quot;
Zhu Yuling, a Sichuan girl who played at home, won a silver medal and failed to complete her goal of defending her title. When talking about whether the enthusiastic home audience would cause invisible pressure on herself, she said: &quot;I think I handled the pressure well during the whole game. Ding Ning played very well today, but he never found his rhythm. &quot;
To activate rural consumption, we must rely on normalized mechanisms to purify the market, guide healthy consumption needs, and enhance farmers&#39; sense of gain in consumption.
Data show that the consumption potential of rural residents continues to be released. In the first half of this year, retail sales of consumer goods in rural areas increased by 10.5%, and the growth rate was 1.3 percentage points higher than that in urban areas.
I visited a poor village in a county in the west. There was only one convenience store in the whole village. When I walked into the store, some of the products seemed familiar. &quot;Golden Arowana&quot; was labeled as &quot;Golden Dragon Oil&quot;, &quot;Wangzi&quot; became &quot;Wangdai&quot;, and &quot;Shanzhai&quot; There are many products.
Over the years, similar phenomena have been exposed frequently. Some fake and shoddy goods in rural areas are similar to famous brands, with similar names and similar packaging. They are fake and real, making it difficult to guard against.
A consumer survey report released by a city in the west shows that the problem of counterfeit goods in rural supermarkets is serious. 66% of users have bought counterfeit goods in offline supermarkets in townships, of which more than half are food products.
Relevant departments are rectifying rural markets and calling for beatings every year. Why do &quot;Li Gui&quot; still keep beating them?
Unlike the urban market, farmers have relatively low awareness of rights protection. In addition, many rural areas are located in remote locations and are in blind spots beyond the reach of regulatory forces, which creates breeding ground for fake and inferior goods.
A commodity is managed by multiple departments. Some departments are in charge of price, some are in charge of production, and some are in charge of market. Their functions are overlapping. Counterfeiting is cracked down every year. There is a centralized management. Counterfeit goods escape the limelight and slowly reappear. Just after the crackdown on old fakes , new fakes pop up again.
The lack of a long-term supervision mechanism makes it difficult to purify the rural market, and the cost of breaking the law is low and the profits are huge. This has led some unscrupulous traders to have the crooked idea of &quot;going to the mountains and rural areas&quot;, and some rural areas have become &quot;waste markets.&quot;
From having enough food and clothing to becoming well-off, the majority of farmers are moving towards development-oriented consumption.
Recently, the Party Central Committee and the State Council issued the &quot;Several Opinions on Improving Consumption Promotion Systems and Mechanisms to Further Stimulate Residents&#39; Consumption Potential&quot;, which proposed to promote the upgrading of rural residents&#39; consumption, with the purpose of making the majority of farmers &quot;able to consume&quot;, &quot;willing to consume&quot; and &quot;dare to consume&quot; , Let rural consumption really flourish.
On the one hand, it is necessary to deepen reforms, eliminate the shortcomings of multiple departments and multi-headed management of market supervision, adapt measures to local conditions, improve food safety and product quality supervision networks, and continuously reduce the space for counterfeiting and selling in rural areas.
On the other hand, we must intensify law enforcement efforts, open up regulatory &quot;capillaries&quot;, and never allow counterfeit goods to breed and spread in rural areas.
Strict punishment for cheating farmers is the only way to protect farmers. No matter how concealed the counterfeiters are, it should not be a reason for the proliferation of fake and shoddy goods. Relevant departments should clarify their responsibilities, lower the level of supervision at the grassroots level, and hold accountable any link that goes wrong. Give counterfeiters and sellers nowhere to hide.
Strictly control market access, implement strict qualification examinations for producers and operators, control market circulation, ensure that products come in the right way and go out clearly, and find ways from the source and root to allow legal dealers to operate with peace of mind and farmers to buy affordable products rest assured.
To activate rural consumption, we must guide healthy consumption demand.
With the upgrading of consumption, many farmers not only pursue full and good food, but also pursue high-quality life such as culture and health. The rural market cannot be equated with &quot;low quality&quot; and &quot;cheap&quot;.
This requires promoting the extension of e-commerce coverage to rural areas, unblocking two-way linked sales channels between urban and rural areas, promoting the integration of offline industry development platforms and online e-commerce trading platforms, supporting the expansion of new consumption formats and models into rural markets; promoting qualified towns and villages to Organically combine commercial logistics with leisure agriculture, rural tourism, product processing, etc.; improve the modern rural circulation network system, optimize and integrate existing facility resources, and effectively reduce rural circulation costs.
Only by creating a clear and reassuring market environment for rural areas, so that farmers do not worry about consumption, can rural consumption become more and more prosperous, and only then can farmers&#39; sense of gain and happiness in consumption be enhanced.
Starting from November 1, my country will reduce the most-favored-nation tax rate for some commodities, and the overall tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%.
According to the decision of the 26th Executive Meeting of the State Council, the Tariff Commission of the State Council issued an announcement on the 30th to reduce the most-favored-nation tax rate for some commodities starting from November 1, 2018.
According to the &quot;Announcement of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council on Reducing Import Tariffs on Certain Commodities&quot;, in order to adapt to industrial upgrading, reduce corporate costs and meet the needs of the public for multi-level consumption, the most-favored-nation tax rate for some industrial products and other commodities will be reduced starting from November 1 this year. .
There are a total of 1,585 tax items on tax-reduced goods, accounting for about 19% of the total tax items in my country. The average tax rate has dropped from 10.5% to 7.8%, with an average decrease of 26%.
This tax reduction mainly involves textiles; stone, ceramics, glass products; some steel and base metal products; mechanical and electrical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, engineering machinery, power transmission and transformation equipment, electrical equipment, instrumentation, etc. ; Resource commodities and primary processed products, such as non-metallic minerals, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, gems and jade, etc.
At the same time, with the reduction of the overall tariff level, especially the reduction of import tariffs on medicines and daily consumer goods, the tax item rates of import taxes on imported items will be reduced accordingly.
In order to implement the decisions and arrangements of the Party Central Committee and the State Council, my country has implemented zero tariffs on most imported drugs from May 1 this year, and has reduced import tariffs on automobiles and parts, and some daily consumer goods since July 1. , implemented the third step of tax reduction for products expanded under the information technology agreement.
The reporter learned from the Tariff Commission of the State Council that since the beginning of this year, after several consecutive independent adjustments, my country&#39;s overall tariff level will be reduced from 9.8% last year to 7.5%, with an average decrease of 23%.
Appropriately reducing tariffs will help promote the balanced development of foreign trade and promote a higher level of opening up to the outside world. It will also help to coordinate the utilization of both international and domestic resources and promote domestic supply-side structural reform.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year marks the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up. Taking the initiative to reduce the overall level of tariffs is a practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping’s important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia. It is also a step for my country to further expand opening up and actively expand imports in accordance with its own high-quality development needs. This important measure shows that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win opening strategy. While enhancing its own development momentum, it will also allow China&#39;s development to better benefit the world.
On September 29, the regional public brand launch conference of &quot;Huanxiangren&quot; agricultural products in Huan County, Gansu Province was held in Nankai District, Tianjin.
Red Army millet, black adzuki beans, mountain boy pastoral black goat, hardcover tartary buckwheat tea, paper-cut shadow puppet album, handmade slippers... Pieces of beautifully packaged agricultural products were neatly placed on the stand. They all have a common brand name called &quot; Huanxiangren&quot;.
&quot;Creating the &#39;Huanxiangren&#39; regional brand has effectively solved the development bottleneck of Huanxian&#39;s agricultural products being &#39;plentiful, scattered, small and weak&#39;, and has become a powerful carrier of poverty alleviation.&quot; On the 29th, the &quot;Huanxiangren&quot; hosted by Huanxian County, Gansu The regional public brand launch conference of &quot;Country People&quot; agricultural products was held in Nankai District, Tianjin.
Huan County is located at the junction of the three provinces of Shaanxi, Gansu and Ningxia. As an &quot;advanced county in grain production in the country&quot;, &quot;the hometown of small cereals in China&quot; and &quot;the hometown of shadow puppets in China&quot;, it has a long history and rich resources.
Local snacks such as lamb meat, yellow rice wine, buckwheat noodles, and soft swallow noodles are the flavors that travelers in foreign lands often think of.
As China&#39;s urbanization level continues to improve and the urban population increases rapidly, a large number of rural young people leave their hometowns and start living in cities.
Yang Qiaojia, a research expert on Chinese agricultural brands, said: &quot;Nowadays, urban life is fast-paced and stressful. More and more people are beginning to miss the rural life of their childhood. However, &#39;what you can&#39;t go back to is called hometown, and the most beautiful memory is the countryside.&#39; Xiangren&#39;s brand design is named after the nostalgia and nostalgia of people wandering around the county. &quot;
Huanxian County has special climatic conditions, long sunshine hours, and large temperature differences between day and night, which provide unique conditions for growing characteristic small grains.
The territory is rich in more than 20 kinds of small grains. It is the hometown of small grains in China. Its output ranks first in Gansu and its quality is among the best in the country.
Wang Xiaoli is a girl from Huanxian County who goes to school in Tianjin. She participated in the promotion meeting as a volunteer. She said: &quot;The people in my hometown are the closest and the taste of my hometown is the most beautiful. The &#39;Huanxiangren&#39; brand evokes so much nostalgia and memories for us.&quot; , what I will never forget is the delicious food there. I hope that the &#39;Huanxiangren&#39; brand will go further and become bigger and bigger. &quot;
Dr. Tan Bin, a researcher at the Academy of Sciences of the State Administration of Grain and Material Reserves, said that through testing more than 900 sets of indicator data, the testing data of agricultural products such as buckwheat, tartary buckwheat, and black beans in Huan County have outstanding advantages. Many cereals contain high levels of physiologically active substances. Based on standard data, &quot;Huanxiangren&quot; has the inherent advantage to seize the domestic high-end grains market.
Chai Chun, Secretary of the Huanxian County Party Committee, said that through the launch of the &quot;Huanxiangren&quot; brand, it can further enhance the quality, standardization, and large-scale innovative development of Huanxian&#39;s high-quality agricultural products, which is conducive to shaping a good overall image of Huanxian&#39;s agricultural products and quickly increasing its popularity and popularity. competitiveness and added value.
Canada&#39;s gross domestic product (GDP) increased by 0.2% in July from the previous month, a higher-than-expected increase, raising market expectations that the Bank of Canada will raise interest rates next month.
If it does raise interest rates, it would be the fifth time the central bank has raised interest rates in a little more than a year.
Analysts polled by Reuters had forecast growth of 0.1%.
Statistics Canada said on Friday that 12 out of 20 industries experienced growth.
The data is noteworthy because the central bank earlier this month predicted temporary factors could weigh on third-quarter GDP data.
Bank of Canada President Poloz promised on Thursday that the central bank will continue to gradually raise interest rates and will pay close attention to economic data.
The Bank of Canada&#39;s next interest rate decision will be on October 24.
With Canada&#39;s economy strengthening and unemployment near record lows, the Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017.
Stephen Brown, senior Canadian economist at Capital Economics, said the country&#39;s economy is expected to grow at an annualized rate of about 2% in the third quarter.
&quot;This would be higher than the Bank of Canada&#39;s forecast of 1.5% and would be another reason to expect the Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month,&quot; he said in a note.
Overnight index swaps showed that the market&#39;s estimate of the Bank of Canada&#39;s probability of raising interest rates in October rose from 76.46% to 78.27%.
South Korea and North Korea conduct joint inspection of Han River estuary for first time in 65 years
South Korea&#39;s Ministry of National Defense confirmed on the 5th that South Korea and North Korea launched a joint inspection of the estuary waters of the Han River and Imjin River that day.
This measure is an early preparation to ensure the free navigation of civilian vessels from both sides.
A briefing provided to the media by the South Korean Ministry of National Defense that day showed that this was the first joint inspection of the Han River estuary since the signing of the Korean War Armistice Agreement in 1953.
South Korea and North Korea signed a military agreement in September this year and agreed to jointly inspect the Han River estuary and other waters starting in November to ensure future environmental protection and tourism development in the waters.
In October, South Korea and North Korea planned a joint inspection of the waters in a general-level meeting.
On November 5, the joint inspection of South Korea and North Korea waters was officially launched.
The joint inspection team consists of 20 people including military and experts from South Korea and North Korea.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, during this inspection, personnel from both sides did not carry weapons and were prohibited from using words or deeds that irritate the other party.
&quot;Because there is no military demarcation line near the estuary, this area used to be an area prone to accidents, but through joint inspections, it will become a new peaceful area in the future. &quot;
The waters covered by this joint South Korea-North Korea inspection are about 70 kilometers long and cover an area of about 280 square kilometers.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, South Korea will send six research ships to detect the depth of the sea water and provide basic information for safe navigation in the waters. After the investigation is completed, it will provide navigation maps for civilian ships.
South Korea and North Korea held a summit meeting in Pyongyang in October 2007 and reached an agreement on the joint use of the Han River and Imjin River estuaries, but subsequent negotiations were stranded due to tensions on the peninsula.
According to the military agreement signed by South Korea and North Korea in September, ships from both sides need to inform each other in advance before sailing in common waters in the future.
China News Service, November 5. According to the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia on the 4th, Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost contact recently while traveling in Mongolia.
It is understood that the two were members of the Blue Sky Rescue Team. On October 19, the two contacted their relatives and friends in China and stated that they were about to go exploring in the mountains near Kusugur Lake. They shared their location through WeChat. Since then, they have lost contact and are suspected to have died. Head to no man&#39;s land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to protecting the legitimate rights and interests and safety of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, and attaches great importance to consular protection and assistance.
After learning about the disappearance of the two tourists, the embassy immediately launched an emergency plan for consular protection, striving to seize the golden rescue time and go all out to carry out the work.
The embassy maintains close communication with the family members of the parties involved, assists the family members in immediately reporting the case to the Mongolian police, and provides the family members with a list of translators for selection.
The embassy immediately met with the heads of the Mongolian Ministry of Foreign Relations, the General Police Bureau, and the General Bureau of Emergency Situations to report the relevant situation and asked the Mongolian side to carry out search and rescue as soon as possible. It also maintained close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure that the latest developments were kept abreast of.
At the same time, the embassy assisted the family members in issuing a missing person notice in Mongolia, and extensively mobilized overseas Chinese and Chinese-funded enterprises in Mongolia to actively participate in the missing person, provided effective clues, and provided relevant assistance to many Blue Sky rescue team members who went to Mongolia to assist in the rescue.
With the strong promotion of the embassy, Mongolia immediately dispatched a rescue team and promised to waive search and rescue expenses.
The Mongolian Police General Directorate and the Emergency Situation Directorate instructed the Khuvsgul Provincial Police and Emergency Situations Department to conduct full search and rescue operations.
Since Lake Khuvsgul is located at the junction of northern Mongolia and Russia, it is remote, vast and sparsely populated, and transportation and communications are extremely inconvenient. Mongolia has now entered a severe winter, with temperatures as low as about minus 20 degrees. The local police and emergency departments Overcoming huge difficulties, almost all police forces were mobilized, and local herdsmen were mobilized to carry out extensive search and rescue operations for days around the location where the two lost contact by riding horses, walking, and visiting herdsmen.
At the same time, in view of the special situation in the pastoral area, Mongolia has been issuing missing persons notices through radio broadcasts for many days.
Relevant staff of the domestic Blue Sky Rescue Team have also come to Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue with the Mongolian side.
The safety of the two missing people has always touched our hearts.
The two have been missing for more than ten days. The embassy has received some clues one after another, but they have not yet been found. The search and rescue operation is still in progress.
The embassy will always adhere to the &quot;people-oriented&quot; principle, continue to pay attention to this matter, push the Mongolian side to continue its full search and rescue, and provide maximum assistance to the family members of the parties involved.
The embassy calls on compatriots and companies in Mongolia to contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia as soon as possible if they learn of relevant clues.
